title: orange dry toast
directions: Mix and shape into loaf.
Bake in greased bread pan at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and slice; lay slices on cookie sheet and bake 60 minutes, 30 minutes on each side.
Watch carefully; they will brown on the underside.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put ground beef, onion and salt in large pan with shortening and mix well.
Stir in chili powder, garlic powder and flour and mix well.
Add tomato paste, water and chili beans and mix together.
Let this cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Add water if it is too thick.
Boil spaghetti as desired to serve with chili.

title: ginger tea
directions: Mix ginger and sugar in cup.
Pour in boiling water.
Stir. Let set about 2 minutes.
Stir again.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Blend in corn syrup and water.
Stir to dissolve.
Simmer gently, 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla extract.
Cool and top ice cream, etc.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In an 11 x 17-inch glass baking dish or a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine 1 1/4 cups water, rice and contents of seasoning packet; mix well.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle evenly with thyme and garlic powder.
Brush with margarine; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil; bake for 45 minutes. Stir in tomato.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer or until liquid is absorbed and chicken is no longer pink inside.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa and water.
Put on stove and bring to boil.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Add eggs, sour cream and cocoa mixture.
Beat well and pour in a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: melting pot minestrone
directions: In a 3 to 4-quart pot, combine onion, red pepper, carrot and sausage.
If sausage is not used, add 1 teaspoon each oil and minced garlic with the vegetables.
Cook over medium-high heat 8 minutes, stirring frequently until lightly browned.
Stir in broth and water, heat to a boil.
Add pasta, cook 8 minutes or until almost tender. Rinse beans and add to broth mixture.
Add tomatoes and zucchini.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Zucchini should be tender.
Arrange bread slices on broiler pan; toast 1 to 2 minutes on each side until golden.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese on each slice.
Heat 1 to 2 minutes more until melted.
Ladle soup into bowls.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and top with a bread slice.
Serves 6.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make 4 sticks, 5-inches long.
Place, uncovered, on baking rack in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake on wire rack for 60 minutes at 300°.
Place a pan under wire rack to catch grease.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or cook on grill.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Place in casserole dish with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, oil, 4 eggs.
In a separate bowl mix 4 cups plain flour, 2 tsp soda, 1 tsp salt, add to first mixture.
Add oatmeal, corn flakes, and pecans.
Mix all together, then drop in about 1 Tbsp on cookie sheet.
Bake 350 degrees for 7 to 9 minutes.
My oven takes 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 150 cookies.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and salt until sugar is melted.
Add pecans.
Cook to soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes; drop onto waxed paper and cool completely.

title: cheeseburger lasagna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook lasagna macaroni according to package directions; drain.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Freeze.
Put in glass; pour 7-Up over.

title: blind bird (rolade)
directions: Cut round steak into 2-inch strips.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place a small piece of bacon and sliced onion on each strip of steak.
Roll up and fasten with a toothpick.
Dip in flour and brown quickly in hot grease (shortening or drippings).
Put on simmer.
Add 1/2 cup water; cover and simmer for about 2 hours. Remove meat from the pan and make gravy from the drippings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in boiling water until tender. Drain.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Saute onion and celery in tablespoon of the bacon fat.
Combine potatoes, carrots, sauteed vegetables, bacon, salt, pepper, milk and half and half.
Simmer for 30 minutes, but do not boil.
Garnish with cheese and parsley.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: orange dump salad (or lime)
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix with cottage cheese and dry jello.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill.

title: north carolina sour cream corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat egg, milk and butter together.
Add milk mixture and sour cream to dry ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are blended.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out of the center of the corn bread clean as a whistle.

title: rise top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onion.
Spread mixture in a 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen custard
directions: Scald milk; mix sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks.
Add scalded milk; cook and stir constantly until thick.
Add vanilla.
Chill. Beat egg whites stiff; add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until creamy. Fold into chilled mixture.
Freeze in freezing compartment.
Can use honey in place of sugar if you like flavor of honey.

title: apple breakfast popovers
directions: Beat together flour, milk, egg whites, margarine and salt. Pour into Pam-sprayed 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in fourths.
Serve with topping made from remaining ingredients heated and stirred until hot.
Serves 4.

title: perk up a potato
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stir soup.
Stir in broccoli, sour cream and mustard.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir occasionally.
Split potatoes; fluff with fork.
Serve sauce over potatoes.
Garnish with chopped pimento.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Place 3/4 head lettuce in bowl, shredded.
Then layer pepper, layer of onion, layer of celery, layer of green peas, then remaining lettuce.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over the entire top and seal edges.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top, then sprinkle crumbled bacon all over top.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese in a medium mixing bowl until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer in each paper-lined muffin cup; spoon cream cheese mixture over wafer, filling cups full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Leave in muffin pans and refrigerate overnight.

title: date squares
directions: In medium saucepan, combine dates, brown sugar and water and cook until soft and creamy.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and lemon rind.
Set mixture aside.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, slightly beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Mix all together and place in covered container.
Do not stir again.
Mixture will keep in refrigerator about 6 weeks.

title: sugar-free banana bread
directions: Mix as you would cake.
Mash bananas; use as a liquid.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a loaf pan at 350°.

title: banana filling
directions: Mix ingredients, except bananas.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Add bananas and cook for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Use on 1-2-3-4 Cake batter.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and sour cream with soda. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together, then add vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill dough well (overnight).
Then roll and use cookie cutter to cut.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 325° until golden brown (about 10 minutes).
I sometimes ice with chocolate icing.

title: holiday peas
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until done.
Add mushrooms and pimiento.
Drain peas; discard liquid.
Add peas to mixture. Add additional butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat thoroughly.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes. In a small bowl, beat egg with fork, add milk and stir.
Put flour in plate.
Salt and pepper tomato slices to taste, dip in milk and egg then flour.
Put oil in skillet, and fry on medium until brown.
Serve while hot.

title: seven-up evergreen bowl
directions: Spoon 3 pints sherbet into your punch bowl.
Let sherbet soften at room temperature for about 5 minutes.
Slowly pour in chilled Seven-Up, stirring lightly, in order to combine with sherbet.
Float generous scoopfuls of the remaining sherbet on top of the punch.
Makes about 36 punch cup servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses; mix at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Mix well; chill several hours and shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: french fried bananas
directions: Peel bananas and brush with lemon or lime juice to prevent discoloration.
Dip it in egg, then in the corn flakes.
Deep-fry in oil heated to approximately 375° for 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel to soak up extra grease.

title: apple salad
directions: In saucepan, boil pineapple and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until mixture is combined.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour into baking dish.
Chill until firm.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Chop onion and green pepper and cook in small amount of grease until soft.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Add potatoes, then remaining ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: daddy's german pancake
directions: Mix flour, milk and salt until smooth.
Add egg; mix until smooth.
Melt butter and shortening in a heavy iron pan with sloping sides.
Add batter.
Bake in 425° oven (preheated) about 12 minutes or until fully puffed and golden brown.
Pancake will not begin to rise before 7 or 8 minutes.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt on stove; let cool.
Add 1 package colored miniature marshmallows.
On wax paper, sprinkle coconut.
Pour chocolate/marshmallow mixture on top of sprinkled coconut.
Then sprinkle some more coconut on top.
Shape into a log.
Refrigerate and slice after cooled.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco in large mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup hot water and eggs.
Dissolve yeast and 1 cup of warm water.
(I add part of the sugar to the yeast mixture.
It helps it rise.)
Add the yeast mixture to the Crisco mixture; mix well.
Stir in flour.
Store in refrigerator in a greased bowl with lid or wet towel.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and make into desired rolls.
Let rise about 2 hours in a warm place.
Bake at 400°.

title: coconut nut topping
directions: Cook in a saucepan for 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread on cake while cake and icing are still warm.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Place onion in blender or food processor.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend together until smooth.
Pour desired amount over shredded cabbage.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese in a crock pot
directions: Cook macaroni and salt for 7 minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients in a crock pot and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken sandwich spread
directions: Add enough mayonnaise dressing to make a good spread.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cut margarine and cheese in flour.
Add water and mix well. Put in cookie press or roll thin and cut into thin strips.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: fruity play dough(this is not edible.)
directions: Warm a skillet to 300°.
Pour water and oil into skillet, bring mixture to a boil.
Add drink mix, flour and salt.
Cook and stir with mixing spoon, knead dough until smooth.
Place play dough in a Ziploc bag to prevent from getting hard.

title: breakfast brunch(serves 10)
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Alternate layer bread, cheese, sausage (about 2 layers).
Mix remaining ingredients (except magarine) and pour over layered dish.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight is best.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: graham-streusel coffee cake
directions: For Streusel:
Combine graham cracker crumbs, walnuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in melted margarine; set aside.

title: baked scones
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, add cut up butter until mixture is rough like corn meal.
Add buttermilk and egg yolks and raisins all at once and mix until combined.
Turn out on a floured board and divide into 4 balls.
Roll each ball into about 1/4-inch circle (like pie shell).
Cut each one into 6 wedges.
Place on baking sheet and brush with egg-wash (1 egg slightly beaten with 1 tablespoon water).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: secret surprise cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour. Beat at low speed until well blended. Chill dough 1/2 hour.
Remove foil from kisses.
Using approximately 1 tablespoon dough per cookie, shape dough around kiss, rolling to make a smooth ball; be sure to cover kiss completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 10 to 12 minutes until cookies are set, but not brown.
Let cool slightly, then remove from sheet.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: brown cookies
directions: Mix in usual manner.
Let mixture stand overnight in cool place.
Roll out to thickness you wish and cut out.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: kellogg's sweet minglers
directions: In large microwave bowl, melt chocolate.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over Kellogg's Crispix cereal.
Place powdered sugar in large plastic bag.
Add cooled cereal to sugar and close bag tightly.
Toss bag until cereal is covered with sugar.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 8 cups.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with Parmesan cheese.
Stir into hot white sauce until melted.
Alternate layers of broccoli and cream cheese mixture in baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into an unbaked crust. Bake 45 minutes at 325°. It is done when a knife comes out clean.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Layer tuna, potato chips, soup, eggs and milk.
Sprinkle thick with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated throughout.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix beef, eggs, onion, bread crumbs, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Shape into 3/4 inch balls.
Heat corn oil in frypan over medium heat.
Add 1/2 of meatballs and brown on all sides.
Brown 2nd batch.
Drain any fat from skillet.
Stir in skillet, tomato juice, corn syrup, lemon juice, oregano, garlic salt and grape jelly.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add meat balls, cover and simmer.
To thicken, mix water and cornstarch together to form paste and add to sauce.
Makes about 90 meat balls.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, salt and sugar, then add a little milk.
Mix and add egg yolks and remainder of milk.
Cook in double boiler. When thick enough, remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shells; add meringue.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: rice krispie date balls (no bake)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and cook on low heat until thickened.	Remove from heat and stir in cereal and nuts.
Let cool.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and save 1 1/2 cups broth.
Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo.
Add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer; add mushrooms with liquid.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Add boned chicken, cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook vermicelli in 1 1/2 quarts chicken broth.
Do not drain.
Mix with all of the ingredients.
Add green peas last so as not to mash peas.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Boil chicken in water with bay leaf, onion, celery and salt. When tender, remove chicken and strain broth.
Add a little more water if necessary.
Add the rice and the remaining vegetables to the broth.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove meat from chicken; cut into cubes.
Add to soup.
A little chicken base or bouillon may be added.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat well all ingredients, except milk, then add milk and blend.
Pour into a greased and floured pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: oven fried parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix milk and egg together. Dip chicken pieces into milk and egg mixture.
Then dip in flour/cheese mixture. Arrange in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour melted butter over chicken and bake 1 hour. Season with paprika and pepper.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg, vanilla and extract. Stir flour with salt and baking powder; stir into creamed mixture. Divide dough in half.
Stir coconut into one half; blend food coloring into remaining dough.
Cover; chill dough for 30 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour, lemon juice and rind, melted butter and the beaten egg yolks.
Add the milk.
Have ready the egg whites, beaten and stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into a pie pan lined with unbaked crust.
Put into a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer or until filling is firm.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans (optional).
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: date nut balls
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Stir often. Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Stir together.
Let cool and roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in 10x confectioners sugar.
Makes about 55 balls.

title: snicker bars
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well. Spread in
an 8 x 8-inch
pan and freeze.
Keep unused portion in freezer.

title: bean chalupa
directions: Put all ingredients in 6 quart Dutch oven and mix well.
Cover and simmer on top of range about 5 hours or until pork is tender. Remove pork and break it up with fork and return it to pot and cook uncovered until thick, about 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.
Serve over corn chips and top with cheese, onions, avocado, tomato, sauces, etc.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine milk and butter in pan. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla and beat in sugar.
Thin with a little milk if necessary.

title: frozen fudge pie
directions: In top of double boiler, melt the chocolate bars and marshmallows with milk and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Fold the whipped cream into the chocolate mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze at least 3 hours.
Garnish with more whipped cream if desired.
Keeps very well in freezer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: roasted white potatoes
directions: Rinse the potatoes and cut in half lengthwise.
Spread them out on a no-stick cookie sheet.
Coat the potatoes with the Italian salad dressing.
Bake at 350°, turning potatoes over frequently; add more dressing if they appear dry.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Measure
water	in 2 cup measuring cup.
Gradually stir in dry milk
until smooth.
Microwave on High 3/4 to 1 minute until steaming hot.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Let cool. Use as you would 1 can (14 ounces) sweetened condensed milk.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash (cut in 1/4-inch slices) in a small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add squash and eggs.
Stir to mix.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and crackers. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate squares over hot water in a double boiler.
Cool.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar and chocolate mixture and blend.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts and mix well.
Bake in 8-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar, let stand 5 minutes.
Add the remaining sugar and all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in 3 cups flour, dough will be soft, let rise double in size and shape in balls and let rise again.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Place cherry Jell-O in a large bowl.
Heat to a boil the red sour cherries, water and sugar.
Add to Jell-O in the large bowl and stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add 1 small can crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Add 1 cold 8 ounce bottle Coca-Cola. Very important that you add the cola last.

title: oreo cream pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello together.
Slice bananas and fill the bottom of the pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip and jello mixture. Top with sliced bananas.
Serve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cover sliced apples with 1/2 biscuit.
Fold and seal like a fried pie.
Place in a sprayed or greased pan or baking dish.
Mix water, sugar, cinnamon and margarine in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: texas creamy pralines
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook in double boiler.
Stir constantly; cook until balls are formed when dripped into a cup of cold water, or until it reaches the soft ball stage on a candy thermometer.
This will take about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add margarine, vanilla and pecans; beat until it is cool and stiff enough to keep its shape when dropped on wax paper.
This may take 15 to 20 minutes of beating.

title: ham stew
directions: In a large pot, combine the first nine ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender. In a small bowl, combine the flour and milk until smooth.
Stir into stew.
Bring to a boil and boil until thickened.
Discard bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Crumble corn bread for the first layer. Add beans, corn, diced peppers, diced tomatoes and diced onion. Sprinkle bacon bits over this. Spread a layer of salsa (hot, medium or mild) over layers. Mix Ranch dressing with sour cream and layer over salsa. Top with cheese and bacon bits.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage and combine with onions, noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds. Make dressing and pour over salad just before serving.

title: prune cookies
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix everything together except prune butter; add more flour to make a soft dough.
Roll some of the dough; cut in squares.
Spread the prune butter from corner to corner of each square, 1 teaspoon or less.
Twist other ends and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender; drain and set aside. Cook onions in the microwave on high for about 2 minutes, until tender.
In a large heavy cooker, combine potatoes and onions with all remaining ingredients, stirring to blend well.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20-30 minutes, stirring often.
Yield:
about 12 quarts.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter in large skillet.
Cover; simmer 35 minutes until tender.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. In skillet gradually stir in vinegar, soy sauce and reserved pineapple sauce.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add pineapple, green pepper, onion and reserved chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp.
Serve over rice.

title: apricot brie
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking sheet.
Layer 6 sheets of phyllo on baking sheet (stagger layers to create a circle), brushing each layer with melted butter.
Place Brie in center of phyllo and spread top and sides with apricot preserves.
Fold phyllo up around the cheese.
Cover top of cheese with 6 sheets of phyllo, again staggering layers and brushing each with butter.
Smooth top and sides, tucking ends under Brie.
Brush top and sides with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand for 30 to 45 minutes before serving.

title: huff's chili
directions: Do not brown meat.
Add all ingredients to water and simmer 4 hours.

title: scotch oatmeal pudding
directions: Making it in a crockery-lined slow cooker is a real winner, followed by the almost-as-good microwave version.
The slow cooker version is ready for eating when you come to the kitchen in the morning.
It's ideal for staggered eating hours.

title: hopeless twinkles
directions: Cream the butter 5 minutes at medium speed.
Add Crisco a little at a time.
Cream another 3 or 4 minutes.
Add the sugar a little at a time while continuing to beat.
Then add the milk, mixed first with the vanilla, beating and scraping the sides and bottom of the bowl frequently.
The longer you beat this the better it becomes.

title: evelyn's tex mex layered dip
directions: To assemble, layer ingredients in order listed in large Pyrex or clear dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate for 2 hours, then form into a ball. Roll in finely chopped walnuts or pecans.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, soda and margarine.
Press 1/2 mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over baked crust.
Mix caramel sauce and 6 tablespoons flour.
Drizzle caramel mixture over nuts and chips. Sprinkle remaining oatmeal mix over top and pat down (lightly) to make a crust.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until melted and golden brown.
Chill before cutting into squares.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Fry hamburger, sausage, green pepper and onion until browned.
Strain grease. Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, mushrooms and garlic powder. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix sauce with noodles.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw 2 loaves of bread dough.
Tear one loaf into pieces and put on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, pudding mixes, milk, cinnamon and walnuts.
Pour mixture over bread pieces.
Tear the second loaf into pieces and put over mixture.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. After baking, flip over onto plate and serve.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake in 350° oven (in low 1/3 of oven) until tester inserted comes out clean, about 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting; can be doubled.
Serves 10 people.

title: flaky southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend chili sauce gradually into cream cheese; mix in other ingredients. Fold in shrimp; cover and chill at least 1 hour. Serve with crackers, potato chips, etc.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onions.
Shape into 6 firm patties.
Cook patties in skillet over medium heat until brown.
Remove from skillet; spoon off fat. Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms.
Return patties to skillet. Cover and cook on low heat 20 minutes or until done.

title: coated pecans
directions: Beat egg whites; add salt and sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Add milk and stir.
Add pecans; stir and coat well.
Put in pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas in microwave (slit package and cook 30 seconds on High).

title: french apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, spices and salt. Stir in apples to coat; pour into crust.

title: canned hot banana peppers
directions: Using clean, wide-mouth quart jars, pack peppers tightly, adding vinegar to cover peppers.
Let set until vinegar fills pepper cavities.

title: brenda's seafood alfredo
directions: Saute scallops and shrimp in butter.
Saute remaining ingredients in butter.
Mix both dishes together and bake in microwave about 7 minutes on High.

title: sweet cucumber relish
directions: Bring to a boil and seal in scalded jars.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onion in a small amount of water until tender.
When done add the beaten egg, butter, salt and pepper. Turn into a greased casserole and spread cracker crumbs.
Some shredded Cheddar cheese on top is a tasty addition.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In deep dish, put 3 cups lettuce.
Sprinkle with tablespoon sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with hard-boiled eggs and salt to taste.
Cover with peas, more lettuce, cover with Swiss cheese, then bacon.
Cover the top with mayonnaise so that salad is sealed completely.
Garnish with garden onions.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Let set 24 hours; toss before serving.

title: basic nonfat sweet dough
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.
In saucepan, heat water, milk and Butter Buds until warm (120° to 130°).
Add with egg to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium.
By hand, stir in 3 cups flour.
Knead in 1 to 2 cups flour until smooth and elastic. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lipton onion soup meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients; shape into loaf in baking dish.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and pour into two greased, floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Using a large skillet (preferably iron), melt margarine.
Add sauce, mushrooms, onion and pepper. Add steak and cook, covered, until steak is tender.
Remove cover and let brown some.
Mix 1 cup water with 2 teaspoons Argo cornstarch.
Add this to pan to make small amount of gravy.
If too thick, add water.

title: delicious apple dip
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in crushed peanuts. Serve with sliced apples. Sprinkle apples with lemon juice to retain color, if desired.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar, salt and beaten eggs. Add vinegar just before pouring into crusts. Bake 10 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 250° and bake until firm, about 25 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Boil broccoli according to directions on bag.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add cheese and mix through.
Bake until bubbling and cheese has melted.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in chopped nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream oil and sugar; add egg and mashed bananas.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into wax paper- lined bread pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheddar bites
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix flour salt, and cayenne pepper good. Add cheese and butter. Form a dough and roll in 1 inch rope. Cut 1/4 inch slices. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until toasty and firm.

title: dressing
directions: Tear bread into small pieces and let dry out.
After frying bacon, remove from skillet,
Saute the onions and celery until tender in the bacon grease.
Add the remaining ingredients (except butter).
Mix well, pour in dish, and drizzle butter on top.
Bake until browned.
May be eaten baked or unbaked.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients, putting okra in last.
Pour 2 inches oil in Dutch oven and heat until 350°.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Turn once.

title: 3-fruit compote
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Drain syrup from fruit and put fruit into a 1 1/2-quart casserole bowl.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
While baking, mix other ingredients.
Pour over fruit and bake for 10 minutes longer.
Good hot or cold.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: foo-foo salad
directions: Mix all together until blended.
Then chill for a short while to set.
Pretty and tastes delicious.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, one egg and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 3 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour on top of crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: candied yam casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut each yam in half widthwise.
Place yams in a shallow greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle yams with peel.
Drizzle syrup over yams and peel.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: mock maple syrup
directions: Simmer cobs in
water 3 hours.
Strain, then add enough water to make 3 quarts.
Add sugars; boil 5 minutes and seal.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Mix together, refrigerate overnight.
Add the Cool Whip before serving.

title: italian twists
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat.
Add sugar, vanilla and rum extract; beat until well blended.
Stir in flour, a little at a time, until dough can be kneaded.
On a well floured board, knead until the dough blisters.
Cut in half.
Roll very thin and cut into strips, about 4-inches long.
Slit each piece in center and pull one end through slit, making sure knot is in the center.
Fry in hot oil until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat the eggs; gradually stir in sugar.
Add meal and flour to mixture.
Add milk and butter.
Stir.
Add vinegar and vanilla. Bake in uncooked pie shell for 45 minutes in 325° oven.
Add nuts if desired.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Bring to a boil the catsup and Pepsi.
Add chicken.
Boil on low.
Cook uncovered until done, about 1 hour.

title: cheese stuffed peppers
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and milk.
Add Cheddar cheese, pickle relish, capers, onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Halve green peppers; fill with mixture.
Slice in wedges. May be served with dressing.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini until done; drain and rinse with cold water until cool.
Chop tomatoes and cucumbers; toss into linguini. Pour Salad Supreme over top; toss lightly (with hands) until well mixed.
Pour Italian dressing over top (slightly toss with hands). Cover and refrigerate.
Let stand a couple of hours; toss again before serving.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Coat spareribs with mixture and marinate 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Bake ribs in flat pan, 1 1/2 hours at 350°, brushing frequently with marinade.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in baking dish.
Add egg one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add pineapple and cubed bread.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour uncovered at 350°.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/4-inch pieces.
Coat with mixture of flour and salt, shaking to remove excess.
Heat oil over medium-high heat in heavy 5 to 6-quart saucepan.
Cook beef 1/3 at a time until brown on all sides, removing to bowl with slotted spoon.
Drain saucepan.
Return beef to saucepan.
Add beef broth, wine, tomato paste, garlic, bay leaves, thyme and marjoram; mix well.

title: sauteed oysters
directions: Salt and pepper 24 selected oysters; dredge in flour.
Grill on lightly buttered griddle on top of stove until crisp and browned on both sides.
Do not broil in an oven.
If no griddle is available, use a heavy skillet on top of the stove.
Sprinkle oysters with butter or cooking oil while grilling.
Do this on both sides, as it browns and crisps them.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Crush candy bars and mix with 2 tablespoons of Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 3/4 of stuffing mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour can of chicken broth over this.
Cut up chicken breasts and layer over the stuffing.
Mix well the soup, sour cream, green onion, green pepper and pimento.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over top and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made and frozen before cooking.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on bottom of uncooked pie crust.
Add pie mixture.
Cover with second crust.
Brush pie with mixture of 1 egg, mixed with 2 tablespoons water.
Bake 50 minutes at 400°. Cool and serve.
Can be topped with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: stuffed pork spareribs with baked apple
directions: Season spareribs to taste.
Cut each slab in two and dust with flour.
Add chopped apple to bread dressing and spread over ribs. Top with tomato slices and onion rings.
Cover the pan and bake at 325° until nearly done, about 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover, baste and brown as desired, baking about 30 minutes more.

title: maple pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and spice; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into dry ingredients just until blended (do not overmix).
Fill paper lined or greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 18.

title: take it easy monday chicken
directions: You will need a Reynolds oven bag (large) for this recipe.

title: appetizer chili rellenos
directions: Mix chopped chili, beef, salt and garlic and fry in oil.
Add water and cook 2 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add egg yolk, salt and flour to whites.
Form meat mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Sprinkle with flour if hard to handle.
Dip balls in egg mixture and fry in oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Freezes well.
Makes 25.

title: sahara special
directions: Mix 2 parts heat with wind.
Add just enough rain to make it unbearable, unless you are specially adapted to arid conditions. Garnish with any variety nomadic people.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes and onion in small amount of water; cover. Cook 20 minutes; drain well.
Mash coarsely.
Combine potatoes and remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Mix well.
Heat thoroughly on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley, chopped.
Good to have in refrigerator on cold night, especially during holidays.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Preheat oven to directions on Tater Tots.
In a frying pan, brown the ground beef.
When browned, add the soup and seasoning salt.
When combined, put mixture in a shallow baking pan.
Cover mixture with
a layer of the green beans.
Cover that layer with Tater Tots and bake according to the directions on the Tater Tots. Serve with a green salad and enjoy!

title: chocolate pixies
directions: In a large saucepan melt butter and chocolate, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool slightly (approximately 15 minutes).
Stir in flour, sugar, nuts, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Add sauce.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Slice zucchini into 1/2-inch slices.
Dredge in flour.
Arrange single layer of zucchini in bottom of lasagna pan.
Combine egg and Ricotta. Spread over zucchini.
Top with half of meat sauce and half of Mozzarella.
Repeat with another of dredged zucchini, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake at 375° for about one hour, until zucchini is tender.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes prior to serving.

title: italian vegetable relish marinara
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Vegetables will be tender-crisp.)
Cool in marinade and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning vegetables occasionally.

title: sweet and savory rice pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, bouillon cubes and soy sauce. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice and dried fruit. Cover immediately and remove from heat; let stand for 5 minutes. Uncover rice and fluff with fork. Stir in almonds and honey. Makes 4 servings.

title: holiday punch
directions: Thaw berries.
Mix together first 6 items in 2 gallon container. Combine water and instant tea.
Stir until dissolved. Add tea to bourbon mixture. Blend berries in blender and add to bourbon/tea mixture.
Let rest for 2 hours (minimum).
Place large block of ice in 3 gallon bowl.
Pour mixture over ice.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Makes 126 (5 ounce) servings.

title: low calorie torte
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add juice concentrate and stir to dissolve.
Refrigerate until thick (about the thickness of an egg white).
Add unbeaten egg whites and beat until fluffy. Pour into graham cracker shell and chill until set.
Try lemon jello and lemonade or lime jello and limeade.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy (light); add eggs.
Mix flour, soda and salt together. Cream bananas till mushy.
Add to butter mixture alternating flour, bananas and pecans.	Pour into well grease loaf pan; bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Check for doneness with a toothpick in the middle.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add flour mixture, vanilla, nuts and drained pineapple.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
If desired, frost cookies with powdered sugar and pineapple juice.

title: diet cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour half in Bundt pan.
Pour 1 small box sugar-free Jell-O (dry, raspberry or any flavor) over batter.
Pour rest of batter over Jell-O.
Bake according to package directions. Approximately 5 grams fat, 130 calories per cake.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Beat 1 cup sugar and butter.
Add egg and molasses. Beat well. Add flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in remaining sugar to coat.
Place 2 1/2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup and bring to a boil; stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add margarine and cool.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into an unbaked deep 9-inch shell; bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then lower to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven pickles
directions: Pack cold.
Finish filling jars with cold water.
Put jars in warm water in a pan in the oven.
Don't let them touch.
Bring to a boil or until they change color.
Check lids for tightness.
Set oven at 225°.
Leave in about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Add enough water to juice from oranges to make 2 cups of liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Melt marshmallows in this liquid and add dry Jell-O.
Let cool.
Mix oranges and cream cheese.
(Mash oranges a bit.)
Add this to first mixture when the batter is partly jelled.
Fold in Cool Whip (mix with mixer) and let the mixture jell now.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream margarine and
sugar.
Add
eggs,
one at a time. Sift flour, salt
and baking powder. Add to first mixture. Add milk. Fold in blueberries. Grease and fill 3-inch muffin tins full. Sprinkle with
mixture
of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes in 350°
oven.
Test
with
toothpick	at
25 minutes. Makes 12 large muffins.
They freeze well.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Shred vegetables.
Mix other ingredients and bring to rolling boil.
Pour over vegetables; cool and refrigerate in covered container.

title: john wayne souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a deep casserole; make layers of cheeses and chilies.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat egg yolks and fold into egg whites.
Gently pour the egg mixture over the cheeses and chilies.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Add drained tomatoes, pushing them down with a fork.
Bake for another half hour.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: mama's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with 1/2 pastry, 1/8-inch thick.
Wash rhubarb and dice into pieces.
Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add egg and beat well.
Add Karo syrup and melted butter.
Pour over rhubarb.
Roll out remaining pastry. Cut into narrow strips.
Arrange lattice of pastry strips across top.
Bake in hot oven.
Heat to moderate at 350°.
Bake 45 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.

title: lauri's chicken bake
directions: Lightly grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together the undiluted soups, minced onion and sherry.
Spread 1/2 cup of raw rice in bottom of the casserole.
Place 3 to 4 pieces of chicken on top of the rice.
Add half of the soup mixture; sprinkle with half the Parmesan cheese.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together potatoes (warm), salad oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and
eggs.	Chill
for
an	hour
or more.	Add chopped radishes, onion, cucumber and mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water; add approximately 6 ice cubes and stir until the Jell-O begins to thicken.
Add all other ingredients.
Let chill in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: sugar and spice bits
directions: Microwave margarine until melted. Add sugar and spices; stir well. Pour sugar mixture over cereal and toss to coat. Microwave, uncovered, 5 to 7 minutes, until heated through, stirring several times during cooking. Stir in raisins and bananas. Cool. Mix will crisp during standing.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients in mixer bowl for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool.
Spread pistachio frosting over top.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Slice tomatoes and arrange on a serving dish.
In a small bowl, combine vinegar, salt, pepper and onion. Slowly whisk in olive oil. Drizzle vinaigrette over tomatoes and sprinkle on shredded basil.
Garnish with sprig of basil.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and sausage; drain and set aside. Combine
remaining
ingredients,
except
chips.
Place on low heat
and
stir until cheese is melted.
Add meat mixture; mix well.
Pour into crock-pot to keep hot.
Serve with corn chips for dipping.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute bacon until fat begins to render.
Add onion, minced garlic clove, green pepper (diced) and celery stalks (cut in diagonal strips).
Saute until limp and golden.
Add tomato sauce, bay leaf, basil, salt, pepper, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce, chicken bouillon, chopped parsley and sugar.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 hour.
Add shrimp (shelled and deveined). Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly, until shrimp are pink and firm.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.
Serving size:
1 serving.
Preparation time:
1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: golden apple bars
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add flour, baking powder, apples and nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and add to mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake shell and cool.
Spread cream cheese on top.
Combine dressing and mayonnaise; cover.
Top with all vegies.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut both green peppers and beef in slices about 2-inches long and 1/3-inch wide.
Presoak beef in 3 teaspoons soy sauce, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Mix and soak for 20 minutes.
Heat 1/4 cup vegetable oil until hot on a pan suitable for stir-fry.
Put in beef and stir-fry until light brown.
Put in green peppers and salt and continue to stir-fry for about 2 minutes on high heat.
(Time varies with temperature of stove.)

title: greek cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Toss Cheddar cheese, grated and some bread crumbs together. Sprinkle over casserole and bake an additional 5 to 7 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Pastry for one crust pie. Line 9 inch pie plate with pastry. Blend first three ingredients. Place in saucepan and cook over low heat until mixture is thick and clear. Cool. Blend cream cheese, sugar and salt. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg has been added. Blend in milk and vanilla. Spread cooled pineapple mixture over bottom of unbaked pastry-lined pie plate. Pour cream cheese mixture over pineapple mixture and sprinkle pecans over top. Bake. Be sure to watch temperature and time on this pie. Bake at 400° for only 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 50 minutes. Serves 6 or 7.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Combine juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add pecans and keep turning until coated and syrup is gone.
Lay out on a cookie sheet.
Separate to dry.

title: oriental green bean casserole
directions: Saute the onion and mushrooms in the margarine in a saucepan. Add the soup, soy sauce, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Heat through.
Alternate layers of green beans and water chestnuts. Pour the soup mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Put the onion rings on top an bake for 5 more minutes.

title: fruited cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add drained fruit cocktail and add instant pudding.
Shape into 2 cheese balls. Wrap in foil and chill at least 8 hours.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: To the flour, add corn syrup and blend until smooth.
Add lightly beaten eggs slowly to the syrup mixture.
Add melted butter slowly; add brown sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Beat about 1 minute, until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 325° oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until filling rises in center even with sides.
Watch closely the last 15 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool on cake rack.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large, deep-sided saute pan, saute the garlic and onion in butter.
Do not brown.
Add the tomatoes and stir.
Sprinkle in flour and stir over medium-high heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in thyme, cayenne, bay leaves and cloves.
Add water and cook another 3 to 4 minutes.
Reduce heat to lowest setting.
Stir in the chicken, ham, shrimp and rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer gently for 30 minutes, stirring once or twice. Add a little water, if necessary, to avoid sticking.
Serves 4 to 6. Great with warm corn bread/muffins.
Fits perfectly in a "Dutch" oven.

title: marinated skewered chicken
directions: Cut boneless chicken breasts into strips.
Marinate in sauce for several hours or overnight.
Thread chicken onto skewers. Broil 5 minutes on each side or until done.
Also good with fresh mushrooms, cherry tomatoes, onion or green peppers for shish kabobs.

title: doug's sinful potatoes
directions: Boil and grate potatoes into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cheese, soup, sour cream and onions.
Mix with potatoes.
Fry and crumble bacon on top of potatoes; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake approximately 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cut up peanuts and dissolve in this.
Drain pineapple and add the liquid to the cold water.
Add first mixture and allow to set partially.
Add whipped Dream Whip and crushed pineapple.
Let sit.
You can also use Lucky Whip or whipped cream if you desire.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening until no sugar grains are left. Mix dry ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg yolks.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add flavorings.
Bake in greased Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.
Can be glazed.
This cake is better the second day.

title: pie shells
directions: Mix sugar and water until dissolved.
Set aside.
In another bowl mix shortening and flour until crumbly, add water mixture. Divide dough into 20, 1/2 lb. balls.

title: dutch refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture and add nuts. Shape in rolls about 2 1/2-inches across.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Slice thin, about 1/4-inch or less.
Bake 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet at 375°.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove at once to rack.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: corn relish
directions: To prepare corn, boil 5 minutes.
Cut from cob.
Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Bring to boil.
Pack in jars and process 15 minutes.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Remove rind from cheese and cut cheese into chunks.
Place all ingredients except garnish in food processor fitted with steel knife.
Process until smooth. Place pate in serving dish.
Chill several hours.
Garnish.
Serve with crackers, party rye or cut up raw vegetables.

title: italian chicken pasta
directions: Cook chicken breast, onions and garlic in large skillet with butter.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Add sauce, stirring and mixing well.
Reduce heat and cover.

title: bavarian mints
directions: Melt all
together until creamy.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into small squares.

title: pecan praline
directions: In a heavy sauce pan mix all cream and sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.

title: fruit dip
directions: Make the pudding with the milk and sour cream.
Mix.
Great with apple slices, melon, grape, kiwi, etc.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Step 1:
Bake cake per box instructions.

title: chopped liver
directions: Slice onions and saute in oil until brown and very soft. Broil livers until cooked, turning halfway through.
Put onions, liver and eggs alternately through food grinder.
Mix well and salt to taste.

title: manhattan clam chowder(from 1975 edition)
directions: If fresh clams are used, scrub and open them.
Chop or grind clams, reserving the juice.
If canned clams are used, drain, reserving juice.

title: gingered pears
directions: Peel, core and cube pears and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix with sour cream, honey, liqueur and ginger.
Serve chilled.
Do not prepare more than 1 hour or 2
in advance, as the pears will get too soft.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain.
Mix Ricotta and cottage cheese with spaghetti.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Press firmly with spoon.
Pour sauce on top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to a full boil.
Add coconut, peanut butter and enough cereal to make balls.
Grease hands with butter and shape into balls about the size of a walnut.
Chill.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Let cool.
Add milk and congeal slightly in refrigerator.
Add all ingredients and let set in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: fried rice
directions: Steam rice, 2 cups water and 1 tablespoon oil in covered saucepan or rice cooker about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand another 20 minutes.
In small amount of oil in wok or skillet, saute chicken until done.
Remove from wok.
In wok, steam carrot, celery and onion pieces in 1/2 cup water until tender and water is absorbed.
Add peas and a little oil and saute a couple of minutes.
Remove all ingredients from wok.
Warm 1/4 cup oil in wok and dump in rice.
Stir and add soy sauce.
Add in previously cooked chicken and veggies.
Green part of onion may be reserved uncooked for garnish.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Press Hershey Kisses into balls. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: layered tex-mex dip
directions: Mix beans with 1/2 cup sour cream. Put them as the bottom layer in your bowl. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning, then layer over the bean dip. Add a layer of lettuce, then tomatoes, onions and black olives. Add layer of salsa or picante sauce. Top with shredded Monterey Jack cheese. Serve with chips.

title: pork chops pizzaiole
directions: Depending on how many pork chops, choose size pot with tight cover.
Grease bottom lightly with olive oil.
Cover with a sprinkle of tomato sauce.
Place a layer of pork chops; cover with thin layer of tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, oregano, cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Place a full layer of thickly sliced potatoes (sliced across whole width of potato, not length) on top of pork chops.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, oregano, cheese, basil, salt and pepper and tomato sauce.
Continue procedure until you have all pork chops and potatoes in pot. Cover tightly; simmer until pork chops and potatoes are tender to the touch.
Serves 2.

title: peanut butter oats candy
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil (medium heat).
When it starts bubbling, cook about 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients dropping by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: impossible pie (coconut)
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, oleo and vanilla; blend well.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle on coconut.

title: orange julius beverage
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container and process for 15 seconds.
This will make 5 servings.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add sugar and baking powder and stir in crumbled Ritz crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased 10-inch pie pan; bake in slow oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Let it get cold, then cover with whipped cream.

title: blueberry - oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal and buttermilk and let stand 5 minutes. Combine remaining dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add egg and oil to oatmeal mixture and stir into dry ingredients only until moistened.
Add blueberries quickly.
Spray bottoms only with vegetable cooking spray 12 medium muffin cups and spoon batter into cups.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling and pour into the 2 pie crusts. Bake about 40 minutes at 375°. Remove from oven and add topping; put back in oven and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Put back into oven and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in buttered dish, uncovered. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: chocolate covered cherry creams
directions: Cover
cherries
in
fondant
by
shaping
2 tablespoons fondant
around
each cherry.
Leave stems exposed for dipping. In small double boiler melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip fondant covered cherries in melted chocolate to coat.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: chocolate chip marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and marshmallow cream in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture starts to boil, cook for 5 minutes.
Immediately add chocolate chips and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Add nuts. Pour into buttered pan.
Cool completely; cut into squares.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Place in a dish a layer of cabbage, onions, and pepper.
Mix vinegar, dressing, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour some vinegar mixture over layer.
Make as many layers as you can. Pour mixture over each layer.
Place in refrigerator, covered, for 24 hours.
Next day, stir well and serve.
It will keep for a week in refrigerator, covered tightly.

title: funky tacos
directions: Return drained ground beef to frying pan.
Add can of beans, spooning all beans and sauce out of can.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes or until hot.
Place half of the cheese slices on top of mixture (spread out).
Simmer on low heat without stirring until cheese starts melting good (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir, then add remaining cheese slices.
Fry corn shells in small pan with oil. Drain on plate with napkins (flat).
Top with meat mixture, lettuce, tomatoes, etc.
(To be compared with tostadas.)

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for only 15 minutes.
In top of double boiler over hot water, melt together caramels, milk and butter.
Pour this over baked portion of cake.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over mixture.
Spread on remaining batter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. If desired, before returning cake to oven, sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans over top of the batter.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Cook the spinach in the butter with the salt until slightly wilted.
Sprinkle with the flour and add the milk and chicken broth; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Puree in a blender or put through a food mill.
Heat with the cream, lemon juice and sugar.
Add more salt if needed.
Serves 4.

title: chicken delight
directions: Pour stuffing mix into melted margarine, stirring well.
Pour half of mixture into bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Heat soups and pour over chicken.
Pour second half of stuffing mix over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-fat breakfast sausage
directions: Combine bread crumbs, salt, sage, ginger and lemon juice in a mixing bowl.
Stir in chicken broth and allow the mixture to soak for 15 minutes.
Mix in the ground turkey and form into patties about 2 1/2-inches round and 3/4-inch thick.
Saute the patties in a nonstick skillet until nicely browned on both sides.
Tastes a lot like regular pork sausage.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake in 2 layers.
Spread mashed berries between layers.
Cool and serve.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients, except meat and cheese.
Spread on top of bread.
Add meat and cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll; place seam side down on sheet.
Brush lightly with beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until brown.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cherry swirl coffee cake
directions: Spray Pam with butter. Spread 2/3 batter, cherries, and other batter into pan.

title: chili & cheese dip
directions: In 8X8 baking dish layer as follows:
cream cheese, chili, salsa, Cheddar, olives.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and spinach crepes
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken, butter, 1/2 cup Velveeta, seasoning and thawed spinach.
Heat through.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Add tomatoes, onion and Ro-Tel.
Cook until onion is done.
Cook noodles, then when done, add noodles and cheese to hamburger mixture.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place flour sifter in 9-inch square baking dish. Sift dry ingredients into dish.
Make 3 wells in mixture.
Into first, put oil, the second vinegar and third the vanilla.
Pour the cold water over top.
Mix with fork just until blended. Don't beat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced instant tea
directions: Mix well and store in tight container and use as needed.

title: golden gravy
directions: Toast the yeast and flour until you can start to smell it. Add the oil and stir while it bubbles and turns golden brown.
Add water, still stirring with a whisk, until it changes to gravy consistency.
Stir in soy sauce, salt and pepper.

title: herbed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend on medium speed until smooth, about 10 seconds.
Refrigerate.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix these ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage mixture and blend.
Let stand 4 hours before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: beans 'n wiener biscuit casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon hot bean mixture into ungreased 9-inch square casserole.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat together slightly.
Pour over top of hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from hot oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool overnight or 4 hours before cutting into small squares.
Serve with dip of Cool Whip, if desired.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix sugar and water together in a saucepan and dissolve over medium heat.
Add nuts.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until nuts are coated with sugar (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Pour into shallow pan one layer deep and bake at 300° for 30 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Simmer hamburger and taco seasoning according to directions and cool.
Stir with next 8 ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate.
Just before serving, add lettuce and chips.
Makes an extra large salad.

title: pineapple 7-up cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together, beat for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.

title: "whipped" pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla, lemon flavoring and sweet milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and then increase heat to 350° and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Roll chicken in sour cream.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roll in Cheez-It crumbs.
Place in casserole dish that has bottom covered in butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: chocolate buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine candy bars and syrup in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts. Stir occasionally; set aside and let cool.
Beat butter at medium speed for 2 minutes (until soft).
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to butter mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix at low speed until blended after each ingredient.
Stir in candy bar mixture and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on rack.

title: spanish rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Leave in pan, covered. Brown well the hamburg.
Add stewed tomatoes and spaghetti sauce. Simmer 15 minutes. Add to rice. Mix well and simmer 10 minutes. Serve. (May not need whole jar of sauce.)

title: mama's chocolate icing(for any 4-layer basic cake)
directions: Cook until hot all ingredients, except the margarine and vanilla,
stirring constantly.
Continue cooking until it drops heavy and thick.
Add margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Cook some more.
Test by dropping a few drops on a saucer to check for spreading consistency.
Start spreading on layers.
It will gradually harden on layers as you spread it on.

title: edith gordon's spinach dip
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan. Rinse sauerkraut in colander with cold water.
Press out excess liquid.
Sprinkle sauerkraut on chicken, top each breast with cheese cut crosswise in half.
Pour salad dressing over this and cover pan with foil.
Bake 40 minutes or until tender with fork. Skim fat, garnish with parsley.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix next four ingredients together.
Add to cooked broccoli and mix well.
Put broccoli mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Combine crackers and butter.
Spread on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn cakes
directions: Combine
cornmeal
and	milk
in
saucepan.
Place over medium heat
and	cook,
stirring constantly until mixture is thick and smooth, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Stir
in egg yolks, salt and white pepper to taste. Add corn. Whip
egg
whites
with
dash
of salt until stiff. Stir 1/4 of whites into cornmeal mixture, then fold in remaining
egg
whites. Thinly
slice
garlic.
Heat heavy skillet, then add
small amount
of	butter.
Ladle	about
1/4 cup of batter into
skillet for
each Corn Cake.
Sprinkle each cake with several
slices
of garlic.
Brown on 1 side over medium heat, then
turn
and brown other side.
Batter is delicate so cook until
set	and use a wide spatula to turn cakes.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Makes 8 Corn Cakes.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In large 12-inch heavy skillet mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Add sweet potatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, basting frequently until syrup thickens and potatoes are glazed.
Serves 8.

title: cheese hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and corn flakes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix butter with corn flakes and put on top of potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Partly cook onion and celery in broth.
In a large bowl crumble cornbread and light bread.
Add seasonings.
Add cooked onion and celery and enough broth to make a medium consistency. Add the chopped eggs and chicken, mix real good.
Bake at 350° until firm, but soft.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soup while cooking.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oriental tuna
directions: Reserve 1/2 of chow mein noodles.
Combine remaining noodles with soup, water, tuna, cashews, celery, onion and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on High or until hot, stirring once.
Top with reserved noodles and let stand 3 to 5 minutes.

title: shirley's cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Blend together remaining ingredients.
Stir together and drop from teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix milk and egg and stir into spaghetti.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vegetable spray. Saute meat, onion, pepper and garlic.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; cook 5 minutes.
Put spaghetti in bottom of baking dish and pour meat sauce over.
Top with mushrooms and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shoestring surprise
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning, corn, onions, shoestring potatoes and water.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with the other pie crust and bake in oven 25 to 30 minutes on 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Heat over low or medium heat while preparing cukes.
Cut cucumbers into 8 pint jars.
Then boil the vinegar mixture for 6 minutes and pour over cucumbers and seal tight.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts.
Wrap each breast in bacon.
Cover the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish with chipped beef. Arrange chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
(At this point it can be refrigerated overnight.)
Bake uncovered for 3 hours at 275°
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients, using 1/2 cup of chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.
Roll into 2 balls and roll each ball in remaining pecans. Store in plastic food wrap in refrigerator.

title: overnight chunk pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in brine overnight (1 cup salt dissolved in 1 gallon of water).
Drain and cut in chunks.
Cook until just hot through in vinegar and water to cover, 2 parts vinegar to 1 part water.
Cook a layer at a time in flat pan.
Pack in jars.
Drain off excess liquid.
Make a syrup to suit your taste as to sugar and spices.
Pour over pickles in jars to cover, having the syrup boiling hot.
Seal at once.

title: lazy biscuits(1935)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Work in lard and milk; beat hard to smooth out lumps. Fill greased gem pans half full. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatora
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Push to side of pan.
Add chicken and brown.
Combine tomato paste, water, salt and pepper; pour over chicken mixture.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add mushrooms and wine (if desired). Cook 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: drew's famous onion dill bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together; warm.
Add rest of ingredients.
If using an automatic bread maker, place dry ingredients in inner pan in the order listed.
Warm the next set of ingredients and add them.
Without an automatic bread maker, hand knead and let this bread rise.
Bake in two loaf pans.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix 1/2 cup cold water with gelatins.
Bring cherries and sugar to boil; remove from heat and add gelatins.
Cool.
(Place pan in cold water with ice cubes until slightly cool.)
After mixture is cool, add pineapple, orange juice and chopped nuts.
Pour in mold and refrigerate until solid.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in pineapple. Add remaining ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Combine boiling water and Nabisco 100% Bran; let stand for 1 hour.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add well beaten eggs, buttermilk and soaked bran.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add all at once with Kellogg's All-Bran.
Fold until ingredients are well moistened.
Store batter in refrigerator.
This will keep at least 2 weeks.
I keep in refrigerator for a few hours before making the first batch.
Bake in greased muffin cups at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add onion, milk slowly, till dough is soft, easily handled. Shape round flat cakes, fry in bacon grease in iron frying pan, or roll into balls, drop into deep fat until brown, crisp.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch dish with 1/2 of the crumbs; press down firmly.
Beat the cheese and powdered sugar together.
Blend peanut butter and milk; mix thoroughly with cheese and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: lumberjack chili
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Combine all in large saucepan with remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Cool.
Add scallions, pepper and olives.
Drain artichoke hearts and reserve marinade. Cut hearts in half and add to rice.
Combine mayonnaise, marinade and curry powder.
Mix well and add to rice.
Store in refrigerator but tastes best at room temperature.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Combine macaroni with remaining ingredients; toss well.
Add more mayonnaise, if necessary.

title: old-fashioned carrot cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar and oil; mix well. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg; beat into egg mixture. Stir in carrots. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips, if desired.
Chill until firm.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: valley ranch ball (double)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, milk and Ranch dressing mix. Blend in cheeses and chill several hours. Roll in almonds and serve with crackers.

title: cheese balls
directions: Keep cheese at room temperature.
With electric mixer, mix all the ingredients.
Chill for eight hours.
Form balls and roll over crushed pecans or walnuts.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine flour, pecans and butter.
Press in pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, 2 cups whipped topping and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer 1 minute or until smooth. Spread over crust.

title: gingered fruit
directions: Drain all cans of fruit.
Place in casserole.
Melt sugar, oleo and ginger.
Pour over fruit and bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: homemade eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy and shiny.
Beat egg yolks until thick and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add to the egg yolk mixture the whipped cream and half and half, stirring well.
Add, still stirring, the liquor if desired.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Dust with nutmeg.
Makes 10 servings about 5 ounces each.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine in a large bowl with sour cream, salt, pepper, onions, soup and cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Put in a greased casserole and cover with cornflakes or Ritz crackers. Pour melted butter over that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nut covered log
directions: You will need a measuring cup, mixing bowl, tablespoon measure, mixing spoon, foil or plastic wrap and a nut chopper or a small knife.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: herb seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a salt shaker and use it to flavor meats, vegetables, starches or anything that you would normally use salt on.

title: coffee carnival
directions: Add tapioca, salt and raisins to hot coffee in a double boiler and cook 15 minutes, stirring.
Add sugar.
When cold and just before serving, fold in cream (whipped).

title: chocolate peanut butter kisses
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat the butter and peanut butter in another bowl.
Add sugar to the butters, mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla, then the dry ingredients.
Blend well, chill the dough.
Form into 60 balls. Roll them in some extra brown sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and place a chocolate kiss on each cookie.
Return to oven for 2 more minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in unsalted, boiling water until tender.
Drain and flake tuna.
Scald milk.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour, then milk.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Add tuna and noodles to white sauce and pepper.
Put in casserole and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Bring to boil pineapple and sugar, remove from heat and add jello and softened cream cheese.
Cool.
Add milk, cherries and nuts.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk salad
