directions: Heat pineapple to dissolve Jell-O.
Cool.
Add buttermilk set in refrigerator to thicken.
Add nuts and Dream Whip.

title: alford's slaw
directions: Shred cabbage. Mix all ingredients together.
Great on hot dogs, hamburgers or with any meal.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in butter, then Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust in a buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust. Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper together; drain.
Mix meat mixture with tomato sauce, paste and garlic.
Heat thoroughly, adding water if needed.
Turn meat mixture into crust.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage sticks
directions: Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese together.
If needed, add water, a little at a time, for desired thickness.
Roll into sticks or balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli.
Remove tough ends of leaves and stalks and wash broccoli thoroughly.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Wash cauliflower and remove green beans.
Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Slice large flowerets into bite size pieces.
Combine vegetables in large bowl.	Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Add mayonnaise mixture tossing well. Chill and serve.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix in blender and pour into greased mold.
Congeal.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water. Make sauce according to directions on package. Toss pasta and shrimp with sauce and serve.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion and ham until smooth.
Separate the slices of ham and turkey, laying 1 slice of turkey on each slice of ham, then spread with cheese mixture.

title: pizza
directions: First you buy our Boboli pizza crust, then you spread your spaghetti sauce on the pizza crust and then you put your ground beef and mushrooms on.
Add black olives, pepperoni and then your last ingredient, cheese.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blue goose pie
directions: Mix above ingredients together and pour into bottom pie crust. Dot with butter.
Put on top crust, sealing edges well.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 50 minutes.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Boil the cabbage for 15 minutes. Change the water and boil 20 minutes longer. Drain and chop fine.
Add eggs, butter, salt, pepper and cream. Stir all together. Bake until brown at 350°.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer.
Or Wassail may be perked in a percolator with spices in the basket.
It is good with slices of orange and lemon.
Refrigerate any leftovers and warm up later.

title: chicken supreme
directions: *I use Uncle Ben's converted rice.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, poke holes all over.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk together; heat in microwave.
Stir and mix well. Pour on warm cake.
Top cake with half of the dried coconut.
Let stand overnight.
Cover with Cool Whip and then remaining coconut. Store in refrigerator.
Best if eaten the following day.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Saute almonds and sesame seed in oil.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage; add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and noodles (broken in pieces) and package of noodle flavor that is in noodle package. Add chicken and onions.
Toss good; let stand overnight.

title: beef jerky
directions: Remove all fat from steak.
Slice with grain 1/8-inch thick. Cook on wire rack at 150° for 4 to 5 hours or until dry.
Line oven with foil.

title: pimento and peas
directions: Drain peas and pimentos. Mix ingredients with mayonnaise dressing and serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: sausage ball appetizers(spicy)
directions: Mix desired amount of Bisquick and milk until just moistened (almost pasty).
Add handful of chopped jalapenos (depending on how spicy you like it).
Add shredded cheese and the browned sausage (crumbled).
Roll into balls (1 teaspoon or so big).
You may need to add more Bisquick if too pasty.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in soup and milk; add macaroni and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts; stir occasionally.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: skillet zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Take two 12-inch skillets and divide recipe ingredients between
them
as
follows:
Melt
butter
in
skillets;
add zucchini
and onion.
Cook until zucchini just becomes tender. Add tomatoes
and
seasonings,
cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from
heat and add cheese and croutons.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Cut
into
pie shaped wedges 6 to a pan and serve. Serves 12.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream(4 or 5-quart freezer)
directions: In a large bowl, combine ice cream mix, condensed milk, eggs (already beaten), vanilla and about 2 quarts milk.
Stir until all mix is dissolved (no lumps), then use electric mixer.
Pour into freezer and add milk to fill line in freezer.
Crank until frozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; do not break apart.
Flatten with rolling pin or hands to fit bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on package.
Cool.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in blender or mixer for 10 minutes.

title: puddingroswell, new mexico
directions: Mix ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: sara's beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in small amount of oil.
Add tomato paste, sour cream and seasonings.
Place alternate layers of drained, cooked noodles and meat mixture in casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: fried tuna patties
directions: Break 2 eggs in a bowl.
Beat eggs with a fork.
Add tuna and mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste and milk and mix.
Add bread crumbs and cracker crumbs.
Put by spoonful in skillet and fry until brown on both sides.

title: best-ever muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl; make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Toss blueberries with two tablespoons sugar and gently stir into batter.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl; roll into small balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: monkey bread(make in tube pan)
directions: Put sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Dip each biscuit, which has been cut into quarters.
Slice margarine and line bottom of tube pan.
Sprinkle with nuts; place each coated piece of biscuit to make a layer.
Cover with nuts; continue until all biscuits are used.
With remaining margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar, bring to a boil; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick and easy hot salsa
directions: Using food processor, add peppers and onion to food processor. Use "chop" setting for approximately 15 seconds.
Add tomatoes and enough juice to make saucy.
Salt to taste.
For milder taste, keep adding remaining juice.
Serve with chips.

title: hedgehogs
directions: Mix dates, nuts and 1 1/2 cups coconut, then add all ingredients.
Mixture will be stiff.
Scoop up a spoonful of mixture and shape into a roll as thick as a frankfurter and half as long.
Roll each in remaining coconut.
Place on greased baking sheet; bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until coconut is just slightly browned, at 350°.
If shaped into a ball and cooked in paper cups, let Hedgehogs cool completely.
They will set as they cool.
Will keep well.

title: fried squash blossoms
directions: Mix batter, using eggs, flour, water, salt, cayenne and turmeric.
Heat the oil in a heavy saucepan.
Dip blossoms in batter until well-coated, then fry in hot oil (375°) until golden brown; takes less than a minute for each.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm.

title: special oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients and stir.
Add oats. Mix well.
You can use a mixer if you like.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 35 minutes.

title: yams with pineapple and pecans
directions: Put raw yams in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle on brown sugar and nutmeg.
Pour on pineapple juice or water.
Cook 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°, depending on yams.
Add crushed pineapple.
Add pecans. Put back in oven to brown for 15 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix well and pinch into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Freezes well.
To reheat, wrap in foil and put in oven.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 cup cheese, onions and chicken breasts (shredded).
Spoon 3 tablespoons mixture into tortillas and place seam side down into an oblong baking dish (spray dish with Pam or something similar).
In 2-quart saucepan, saute green chilies in 1/4 cup margarine (until simmering).
Stir in 1/4 cup flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in chicken broth; cook on medium-low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Pour mixture over tortillas and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup remaining cheese over dish and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate meringue crisp
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add sugar and vanilla. Crumble chocolate snaps in bowl and add baking powder and nuts. Fold egg white mixture into this.
Pour into greased pie plates and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: scrumptious pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add salt, pumpkin and sour cream, stirring well.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir into pumpkin mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff peak forms.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 55 minutes more.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread evenly in pan.
Refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours).
Remove and allow to come to room temperature. Cut into bars.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix all ingredients and pour in pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eagle brand pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until blended well.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add Eagle Brand milk and flour gradually to egg mixture; add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: ethel's coconut - pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter or margarine and vanilla in a sauce pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Cook until thick enough to spread.
Beat occasionally.

title: rocky road freeze
directions: In a small bowl, mix sweetened condensed milk and chocolate syrup. In a separate mixing bowl, beat whipping cream until stiff peaks form. Fold in chocolate mixture, marshmallows, chocolate chips, and nuts. Transfer to a freezer container. Freeze for 5 hours or more. To serve, remove from freezer 10 min before serving. Store in freezer for up to 2 weeks.

title: butterscotch-rice mold
directions: In saucepan, combine pudding mix, salt and cinnamon.
Slowly mix in milk, add uncooked rice.
Cook, stirring over medium heat. Simmer 2 minutes more.
Soften gelatin in water and add to pudding mixture.
Cook and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Turn into 4 1/2 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Yields 7 servings.

title: shrimp and mushrooms au gratin
directions: In
measuring
cup
or	small
bowl
combine milk, clam juice, sherry
and
seasonings; set aside.
In 9-inch skillet heat 1 teaspoon margarine until bubbly and hot; add shrimp and saute until
shrimp turn pink, about 3 minutes.
Divide shrimp into 2 (1/2 cup) flameproof ramekins or shallow baking dishes. Keep warm.

title: potato dressing
directions: Use only hot fluffy potatoes and combine with the other ingredients.
Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° until browned. This is delicious.
Should be served immediately out of the oven.

title: humitas(corn)
directions: Mix the grated corn with the beaten eggs.
Add butter, cheese, salt and sugar; mix well.
Place a tablespoon of this mixture in the center of each leaf and roll well in the leaf in the form of an envelope, tying the square with strings of the same leaf.
Cook for half an hour in a double boiler.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Mix and bake in unbaked pie shell for about 40 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: super easy pineapple or banana cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and bake in greased Bundt pan for 50 to 55 minutes.
Warm confectioners sugar, margarine and 1 1/4 cups water until margarine melts and pour over hot cake.
Let set a while and take out of pan and eat!
Eat!

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain off grease.
Saute vegetables until tender.
Boil rice, noodle soup and water for 7 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1 cup of shredded cheese and pour into casserole dish, 9 x 13-inches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast primavera
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Tear off large piece of tinfoil and lightly coat with oil.
Place breasts on oiled side.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with bell pepper, green beans, peas and onions.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle over the Parmesan.

title: candice's favorite loaded white potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 300° for 20 minutes.
Wrap potatoes in aluminum foil.
Place in heated oven.
Cook until fork passes through center of potato without resistance.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix according to directions on box in 9 x 13 pan. Allow to cool completely.
Use fork to prick holes in the top of cooled brownies.
Mix sugar and coffee; drizzle over brownies. Break brownies into small pieces.
Place half in the bottom of a large glass serving bowl.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake as package directs, using 1/2 cup creme de menthe as part of the liquid.
Bake and let cool.
Spread 1 can Hershey's fudge sauce over top of cake.
Mix 2 teaspoons creme de menthe with Cool Whip and spread over top.
Better made a day in advance.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press into large cake pan; chill 15 minutes.

title: seasoned croutons
directions: Stir in large container.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: scottish bachelor's almost scones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Chop up margarine in as small pieces as your patience will allow.
Attempt to mix evenly into dry ingredients.
Mix egg whites, honey, milk and treacle.
Pour into other ingredients.
Beat ingredients with a heavy spoon until you get tired of it.
(If it looks too thin, add some more oats.
If too thick, add milk.)
Spoon into greased muffin tins (they run all over cookie sheets!).
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with margarine.
They will be a bit chewy.
They freeze okay and microwave hot again.
Makes about 24 large scones.
Enjoy.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and milk and put in a 3-quart casserole.
Put chicken on top, skin down.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours.
Turn chicken once.

title: four-in-one cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon (or larger) onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream. Serve over rice. Add sour cream before serving.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine limeade powder, sugar, water and pineapple juice in large container; mix well.
Pour over ice cubes in large punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale.
Garnish with sprig of mint or maraschino cherries.
Serve immediately.
Makes 75 servings.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream the butter and both sugars. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Add chips, grated chocolate and nuts. Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: no cook marshmallow icing
directions: Beat egg whites and salt with electric mixer until foamy. Gradually beat in sugar, beating until mixture is smooth and glossy. Beat in Karo syrup, a little at a time. Beat until frosting peaks when beater is raised. Fold in vanilla. (Add food coloring if desired.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set for 12 hours or overnight.

title: hungarian gulyas (goulash)
directions: Brown onions and meat in hot fat, butter or olive oil.
Add flour, tomatoes and spices.
Cover and simmer four hours or so until meat is tender.
If liquid is needed, use some of the wine left over from the lasagne.
Stir frequently, particularly during the last stages of cooking.
Remove from heat, add sour cream and serve over boiled new potatoes, dumplings or buttered noodles (sprinkled with poppy seed if there's any around the kitchen).
My preference is noodles.

title: lauriann's stuffed mushrooms
directions: In a large frying pan, mix clams and butter and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add Worcestershire, garlic powder, shake of marjoram and thyme (not necessary) and 3/4 cup of white wine.
Simmer for 10 more minutes.
Turn off heat and add bread crumbs, parsley and paprika for color and 2 handfuls of Parmesan cheese; mix immediately.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken in roaster.
In small frypan, saute garlic and onion in oil or butter.
Pour over chicken parts and sprinkle with oregano, parsley and herb dressing.
Mix tomatoes and pizza sauce together and pour over chicken.
Cover with lid.
Bake 2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: columbian spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain.
Add salt, sour cream, margarine and cheese.
Mix well and pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven until mixture bubbles and bread crumbs have browned.

title: molasses cookies - gingersnaps
directions: Melt and cool shortening.
Add sugar and molasses.
Add egg mix and beat well.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Mix well with first mixture and chill for about 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix 1/2 stick of melted margarine, Ritz Crackers, and poppy seeds. Place 1/2 of this cracker mixture in a 9x13 baking dish. Cook & shred 4-6 chicken breast. Add Cream of Chicken soup and sour cream mixing together well and place over the cracker mixture. Add the remaining 1/2 of the cracker mixture to the top of the chicken mixture. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 45-60 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, oil and dry ingredients.
Mix. Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, toothpick inserted in center.

title: lemon slush
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in bottom of pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over crust.
Mix pudding mix and milk and beat until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Put rest of an 8 ounce Cool Whip on top.

title: angel fruit salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients by hand and chill.

title: tuna corn chowder
directions: Saute chopped onion in tuna oil (drained off).
Add potatoes, salt and enough water to cover.
Cook until done.
Add all other ingredients and heat through.
Serve with warm crusty bread or rolls and butter.

title: watkins tea biscuits
directions: Beat butter and sugar to a cream.
Add the well beaten egg, salt and milk and sift in the flour and baking powder together. Dough should be very light, but if too soft, add a little more flour.
Roll out on a well floured board and cut out with a biscuit cutter.
Place close together in a shallow pan.
Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: german pizza
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Shred potatoes to fill large lifetime pan.
Add salt and pepper. Cover with any leftover meat, cut bite-size.
Stir eggs together with fork.
Pour on top.
Turn heat up until lid is warm, then simmer until potatoes are done.
Put cheese on top. Let melt.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Brown ribs on all sides in skillet.
When frying, sprinkle garlic salt and pepper over ribs.
In a large kettle, put 1 jar barbecue sauce, onion and garlic.
Simmer.
Add ribs when brown, then add other jar of barbecue sauce.
Rinse out jars with 1/4 cup water.
Add to ribs and sauce. Simmer until ribs are done.

title: cream cheese ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, while beating. Add milks, cream, cream cheese, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Freeze according to freezer instructions after filling freezer can with whole milk.

title: carrots and celery with pecans
directions: Combine water and salt; bring to a boil.
Add carrots; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until desired tenderness. Add celery and cover; simmer an additional 5 minutes or until celery is crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Saute pecans and dill weed in butter until pecans are golden.
Toss with carrots and celery. Yields 6 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cover chicken with water in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cool.
Bone chicken, shredded in large pieces.
Add to broth.

title: pear cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, vanilla and vegetable oil and beat well. Combine flour, soda, cloves, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sift together.
Add to original mixture.
Fold in pears and pecans. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° until done, about two hours.

title: belgian cherry cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, extract and milk.
Blend in flour and mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and insert cherry half into center of ball.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased baking sheets until set, not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar, cool and roll again.

title: white sauce for cauliflower
directions: In a small saucepan stir cold milk and flour together until flour is completely mixed in.
Add butter and salt, heating slowly while continuously stirring until sauce thickens.
Pour over cooked cauliflower.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion; drain, then add dry Hidden Valley Ranch seasoning and dry taco seasoning to the cooked ground beef. Combine all other ingredients in a large pot. Add in cooked ground beef and allow to simmer for 30 minutes. Great served with tortilla chips and shredded cheese.

title: church window candy
directions: Combine chocolate pieces and margarine over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
Divide mixture in half.
Shape each half into a log.
Roll each in remaining nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap. Chill.
Cut into slices.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients together. Flour and grease Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Combine.
Beat until creamy and combine the 2 mixtures.
Beat; then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: old fashion chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut into squares. Ice with chocolate.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and sugar.
Dissolve in milk.
Scoop ice cream into mixture and stir to partially mix.
Leave some lumps of ice cream.
Gradually add club soda just before serving.

title: moist and crispy chicken
directions: Place soup mix and crumbs into bag; shake to blend.
Dry chicken; brush with mayonnaise.
Place chicken in bag; shake until coated.
Bake on rack in roasting pan at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: robbie's company beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening in heavy skillet until all red color disappears.
Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni, while other simmers, according to package directions.
Combine macaroni and beef mixture in a baking dish.
Season to taste. Gently spoon cream of mushroom soup into mixture.
Mix lightly, lifting from bottom.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, until top is bubbly and browned. Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and parsley in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients with enough water to cover rice 1 inch. Cook until most of juice is gone.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Don't lift the lid for at least 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain excess fat.
Stir in seasoning mix.
In salad bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Add meat and toss; add taco sauce to taste.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Crumb the crackers and mix with the melted margarine.
Set aside 1 cup. Soften ice cream until creamy and add milk and pudding mix.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers.
Mix and pour mixture over the crackers.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip and the 1 cup crackers. Keep refrigerated.

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Combine zucchini, green pepper, celery, onion and red pepper in a medium bowl.
Set aside.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry ground beef in a skillet with chopped onion and green pepper on medium heat.
Stir periodically to keep it from sticking.
Drain properly.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Transfer to bowl and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
This recipe makes 2 thin filling pies or 1 deep dish pie.
You can double the recipe and make 3 deep dish pies.

title: cooked dressing for potato salad
directions: Combine sugar, water, vinegar, oleo, eggs and salt.
Cook on stove to a boil.
Continue cooking 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and cool.
Add salad dressing.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1/2 cup 10x sugar and 1/2 cup margarine together.
Put a layer of crumbs on bottom of pan.

Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip, 1/2 cup 10x sugar, vanilla and milk together. Put a layer of cream cheese mixture on crumb crust, then the pie filling, then another layer of cream cheese mixture and then the remaining crumbs on top.
Chill for several hours.

title: cajun mushrooms(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Wash mushrooms and bring ingredients to boil; add mushrooms and boil on high 10 minutes, then simmer 20 minutes. Let stand for 1 hour.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream all shortening.
Add spices, soda, baking powder and eggs.
Gradually add flour, buttermilk and remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: springtime asparagus
directions: Mix mushrooms, dressing and lemon juice in large nonstick skillet.
Cook on medium heat 3 to 5 minutes or just until mushrooms are tender, stirring frequently.
Top with asparagus. Cover, reduce heat to medium low, simmer 5 minutes or until asparagus is crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: ice crem
directions: Put ice and milk into the blinder and stir.
Then you have your on ice cream.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in heavy frypan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tequila lime punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine water, tequila, juices and sugar until thoroughly blended.
Pour chilled pop down the side of the bowl; stir gently to blend.
Garnish top with lime and orange slices.
Serve over ice in punch cups.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend, then pour into precooked and cooled pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
You can freeze one.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, beaten egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and put in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and sauce.
Pour over loaf; bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add ingredients in order.
Mix mayonnaise and salad dressing, then toss to coat.

title: salmon appetizers
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove bones. Combine all ingredients.
Spread 2 tablespoons mixture over each tortilla. Roll each up and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Slice each tortilla into bite size pieces.

title: cheesecake
directions: Place ingredients in order in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer. Start on low, move to medium and finish for 10 minutes on high.
Batter should be a smooth liquid.
Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch spring-form pan (3-inches high).
Bake for 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
Leave cake in oven with door closed for an additional hour after heat is turned off.
Cool on rack and refrigerate.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together grated cabbage and carrots; add sugar, vinegar, salt and mayonnaise.
Chill and serve.

title: red velvet punch
directions: Mix the cranberry juice, pineapple juice, orange juice concentrate and lemon concentrate in a large container. Chill, covered, for 8 to 10 hours. Pour into a punch bowl. Stir in the ginger ale.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and blend.
Make paste with food coloring and cocoa; add to mixture.
Sift flour and salt together.
Then with electric mixer at medium speed, add alternately with buttermilk and flavorings.
Blend well.
Mix soda and vinegar together; add to batter, stirring gently.
Bake in two 8-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to a boil in medium-size saucepan.
Add grits, salt and pepper. Return to boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese, butter, milk, eggs and garlic, stirring until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes more.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: oriental green bean
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute vegetables until tender. Drain liquid.
Melt stick of butter.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add 4 tablespoons flour.
Stir in milk/mushroom juice.
Simmer until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add Cheddar, soy, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
In casserole, combine beans, vegetables, cream sauce, crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle French fried onion rings on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter, eggs and vanilla together. Pour in crust.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together eggs, butter, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add flour and zucchini; batter will be thick.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Cook raisins and water for 10 minutes. Add egg and nuts to raisin mixture. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Combine sugar and shortening to dry ingredients. Fold in raisin mixture; fill 3 (No. 2) cans 1/2 full. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with crumbs.
Pat into 9 x 13 pan.
Beat remaining butter, vanilla and powdered sugar for 10 minutes.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Cover with cut bananas and pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Store in refrigerator for 13 to 24 hours.

title: squash pickles
directions: Cut squash into 1/4 by 2-inch stripes.
Mix 2 teaspoons alum in 1 gallon of water.
Put in squash and let stand 2 hours. Remove and wash in cold water.
Mix sugar, dill, vinegar, turmeric and salt.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Put in squash and let simmer 3 minutes.
Let stand one hour; then put in cans and seal.

title: buttermilk loaf cake
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in vanilla, lemon juice and rind.

Sift together the dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Turn batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place onion and garlic in a medium saucepan coated with cooking spray.
Cover; cook over low heat for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Add tomato and next 4 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Set aside.
Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Flatten to 1/8-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Combine flour and Parmesan cheese in a shallow dish.
Dip each piece of chicken in egg white; dredge in flour mixture.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook for 2 minutes on each side, or until browned.

title: green chili steaks
directions: Brown
cubed
steaks
on
both
sides
and
set
aside. Combine oil and flour in a saucepan; brown well.
Add milk and chopped green chile, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add garlic
powder and salt to taste; stir.
Place cubed steaks in a casserole and pour gravy over.
Warm in oven.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, bring 1 inch salted water to a boil.
Add potatoes; return to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain water from potatoes; return to low heat.
Gently shake pan just until potatoes are dry.
Remove from heat.
Mash potatoes until smooth. Stir in butter, salt, pepper and enough milk to make moderately stiff mashed potatoes.
Spread in greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Evenly spread whipped cream over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 425° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Place 1/2 package of stuffing on bottom.
Mix together squash, salt, pepper, beaten eggs, soup, sour cream, half of cheese and 1/4 of the stuffing; pour over crumbs.
Add 1/4 package stuffing, sprinkling on top.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: five minute chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Arrange the chicken pieces in baking dish; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix together the mayo, soup, mushrooms, wine, garlic, parsley, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until done.
Sprinkle with paprika just before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Put half jello mixture in dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread layer with cream.
Add remaining jello mixture; chill until firm.

title: chicken with pecans
directions: Poach chicken breasts.
Remove meat and put in baking dish. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onions and celery.
Pour over chicken.
On top, put buttered toast, cut in pieces, and pecans. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Save 1 cup of juice from berries and pineapple.
Mix well jello and boiling water.
Add juice and mix well.
Jell, then top.

title: bermuda triangle burgers
directions: Slice onion in 8 thin slices.
Form 16 hamburger patties 1/2-inch larger than onion slices.
Place 1 patty down; put onion on top.
Add mustard or whatever you like on your hamburgers. Cover with other patty and seal edges by crimping.
Fry or bake. Serves 8.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch crust. Bake at 350° until glaze forms on top, about 45 minutes.

title: spinach dressing
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat and cook; pour off fat.
Add spinach, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
This can be used to stuff turkey for a different taste.
Dr.
Sengelmann told me about it and I love it.

title: herb-crusted lamb with roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat
the oven to 425°.
Cut slits all over the lamb with the tip of a sharp knife and insert the garlic slivers in the slits.
Brush
the lamb all over with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.

title: twice baked acorn squash
directions: Wash squash.
Cut in half and remove seeds and membranes.
Lay squash cut side down in a microwave dish.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High for about 9 minutes.
Carefully turn squash over and add a pat of butter.
Sprinkle some brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Return to microwave and cook on High, covered, for about 4 minutes, until cooked.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve in shells.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, bring evaporated milk just to a boil.
Add chocolate chips, return to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted, slightly thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and salt.
Serve warm as a dipping sauce for fresh fruit, or spoon over cake or ice cream. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: foil-wrapped herbed chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken on a piece of foil.
Add onion and uncooked rice in desired amounts.
Add Kitchen Bouquet to soup; place over rice.
Add seasonings; seal closed.
Bake foil bags at 450° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan date spread
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine margarine and cream cheese.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with crackers or nut bread.
Store refrigerated.
Yields 1 cup.

title: scrambled eggs texas style
directions: In a bowl mix eggs and milk.
Put the burner on medium heat. Spray the skillet with Pam.
Pour the eggs into the pan.
Quickly add the pepper, salt and garlic powder.
Before the eggs set up completely put in and stir the salsa, finely chopped mushrooms, salami and a teaspoon of horseradish.
Stir the eggs until they set up and serve.

title: thin peach tart
directions: Combine
flour	and
salt
in a bowl.
Cut in margarine with a
pastry
blender	until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle water
and	1/4
teaspoon vanilla.	Stir with a fork until	all dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into a ball and press into a lightly greased pie plate.
Set aside.

title: mildred's grilled chicken
directions: Preheat broiler, line it with foil.
In a medium sauce pan, combine tomato juice, tomato paste, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce, horseradish, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat, uncover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Coarsely chop scallions and tomato.
Place chicken on broiler, spoon half of sauce over chicken and grill 4 inches from heat until chicken turns brown.
Stir in scallions and tomato in the remaining sauce.
Turn chicken over and spoon remaining sauce on chicken.
Cook 4 inches from heat until brown, about 12 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add nuts and dates (which have been cut into small pieces). Boil 10 more minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let cool.
Beat until thick enough to pour on damp cloth.
Roll up in cloth.
Cut when cool.

title: chicken and sour cream
directions: Simply mix a container of sour cream and a can of cream of mushroom soup.
Mix in chicken.
You may top with crushed crackers and poppy seed.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Great served over brown rice.
Makes own gravy.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish lightly with Pam.
Layer potatoes, onions, peppers and cheese.
Add a layer of ground beef and cream of mushroom soup.
Continue to layer ingredients until they are gone.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese puff
directions: Place bread in shallow pan; cover with cheese.
Repeat.
Mix eggs, milk and Worcestershire sauce and pour over bread and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust (pressed into round glass casserole dish).
Cover with second pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, soften yeast in warm water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
With a pastry cutter, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; mix well.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk; stir until combined.
On a floured surface, knead mixture about 2 minutes or until smooth, adding more flour as needed.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Using a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, cut out 24 biscuits.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 450° oven about 8 minutes or until biscuits are light brown on the bottom.
Makes about 24 biscuits.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, nuts, pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker pie crusts.
Decorate with pecans and maraschino cherries, if preferred.
Chill before serving.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, whisk together sugar, oil and eggs.
Whisk in potatoes.
Mix dry items together.
Add dry items to creamed items and buttermilk.
Spoon into cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until done when tested.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto plate, dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: red lobster cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine buttermilk baking mix, milk and shredded Cheddar cheese with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Moisten with mayonnaise and add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: crepe suzettes
directions: Combine sifted flour, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add the whole eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add enough milk to make a thin batter.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in melted butter.
Pour about 1/2 cup batter into a heated lightly greased skillet.
When brown on underside, turn and brown on other side.
Spread with marmalade and roll.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine and mix well in large bowl, the rolled oats, flour, sugar and salt.
Over this mixture, pour the melted butter.
Mix well and then add the beaten eggs and vanilla.
Cover a cookie sheet with aluminum foil and drop the cookie mixture by 1/2 teaspoon two inches apart on the foil.
Bake in preheated 325° oven about 8 to 10 minutes.
When cookies are completely cool, foil will peel off.
Store in airtight container.
This recipe makes at least 6 dozen cookies.

title: dream salad
directions: Blend cottage cheese with Cool Whip (use mixer).
Slowly add jello, pineapple chunks and pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: double crispy chicken
directions: Measure corn flakes into shallow dish or pan.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, beat egg and milk slightly.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter.
Coat with crushed cereal.
Place in pan, in single layer, skin side up, in greased or foil-lined baking pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover pan or turn chicken while baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven in hot oil, brown meat on both sides.
In medium bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour broth mixture over roast. Bake, covered, with foil or ovenproof lid at 350° for 3 to 4 hours or until meat is very tender.
Drain fat.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together in one bowl by hand.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° in jelly roll pan for approximately 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: better-than-almost-anything cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Using a 13 x 9 inch pan. Cool 15 minutes. Poke top of warm cake every 1/2 inch with a handle of wooden spoon.
Drizzle sweetened milk evenly over top of cake.
Let stand until milk has been absorbed into cake.
Drizzle caramel topping cover and refrigerate about 2 hour.
Spread with Cool Whip on top of cake.
Sprinkle with toffee chips, cover and refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick mix, eggs, margarine and vanilla in blender; cover.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle with coconut.
Sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.
Bake 40 minutes or until knife comes out clear when inserted.

title: cape cod oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Beat egg; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Arrange by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in moderately slow oven (325°).
Yields about 75 cookies.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need 1 garden spade, 1 new 8-inch flowerpot and 1 or 2 silk flowers.

title: sweet-n-sour bacon curls
directions: Bake additional 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve.

title: brownie bar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and eggs.
Add sugar, cocoa and canned milk. Stir well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Beat until very light.
Bake at 300° for about 30 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 5-inch pan.

title: 1-2-3 fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring vigorously.
Remove from heat and beat with rotary beater for 1 minute.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Melt shortening in a skillet.
Combine 1/2 of the shortening with rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour into hot skillet. Bake at 400° until done.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise as directed, using enough to mix well.
Serves 8.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix well and pat into pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch and cocoa with a small amount of the milk until smooth.
Add remaining milk, stirring well.
Microwave on High, stirring 3 or 4 times during cooking time.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown in conventional oven.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and melted margarine until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except crescent rolls. Separate rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle; pull the 4 corners to center and seal.
Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle with croutons if desired.
Bake on ungreased sheet 20 to 24 minutes or until golden.

title: egg casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine milk, eggs, dry mustard and salt. Beat for 1 minute.
Stir in cheese, bread and ham.
Pour into ungreased 11 x 17-inch loaf pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 12. This can be mixed and refrigerated ahead of time.
Add 5 to 10 minutes for baking if refrigerated.

title: coffee loaf
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl. Gradually add milk, butter and vanilla, mixing well. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until cake tests done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: jim's sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion; stir often to assure fine crumbling of meat.
(I use a Rubbermaid colander inserted in a large measuring bowl in the microwave; the fat and any water drains through to the bowl.)
In a separate pan on low heat, add the meat and next 3 ingredients and stir.
Add ketchup, stir and simmer.
Serve on buns, or as a meat dip with chips.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Add ingredients as instructed on package. Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 350°.

title: hardtack
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients, then add last 3.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in small amount of oil.
Set aside.
Peel potatoes, cut in half and season.

title: hamburger-noodle hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and green peppers and drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine celery soup, mushroom soup and beef broth.
Combine all ingredients, then add cheese.
Let it melt while cooking over medium heat.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: pork pot orange
directions: Lightly salt and pepper each chop.
Brown chops on both sides in a large skillet.
Drain fat.
Mix sugar, water, orange peel and juice, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over chops.
Place an onion slice and an orange slice on each chops.
Simmer, covered, on low heat for 1 hour.
Remove chops.

title: italian macaroni
directions: Place beef roast in a large, heavy kettle with butter or margarine; brown all sides.
Remove meat.
Add onions and thinly sliced garlic; cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste and bay leaves.
Return meat to kettle; cook very slowly, until sauce has a thick texture.
Salt to taste.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Chop half of the strawberries with a knife and the other half in the food processor.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to the dry ingredients, stirring until well combined. Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 9x5x3 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.
Cool loaves in pans about 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks. Yield:
2 loaves.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Wash broccoli; drain.
Trim stalks and split into spears.
In a large pot, bring water to boiling and cook broccoli for 5 to 7 minutes until tender; drain.
Place cooked stalks in greased casserole dish.

title: pelican pineapple dessert
directions: Layer crushed pineapple, diced	cream cheese and marshmallows in baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour together, stir in pineapple juice and beat in egg.
Cook mixture slowly, boil until very thick, stirring to keep from sticking.
(Double boiler works well.)

title: old fashioned grandma
directions: Mix with a grandchild's love and kisses.
Place in rocking chair on front porch.
Yields:
1 old fashion Grandma Ate.
This recipe will come out very sweet especially if the temperature is warm.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the Bleu cheese, in a food processor and process until fluffy.
Add cheese and process until almont smooth.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat 1 cup water, add broccoli and cook 5 minutes; drain.
Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and peppers in greased 10-inch pie plate. Beat rest of ingredients 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 400° oven or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut up when done.
Mix all liquids together and add chicken to mixture.
Layer in baking dish the Doritos (crushed), then all the mix and another layer of crushed Doritos. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peach slush
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil.
Add 4 tea bags.
Steep for 5 minutes.
In a large pot, heat 7 cups of water and add the sugar and tea water, then add lemonade and orange juice.
Let cool and add 2 cups Peach Schnapps.
Pour into large container with lid and put into freezer.
Freeze overnight.
Put scoop in glass and add ginger ale.

title: banana chocolate ripple cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Blend in egg yolks, bananas, vanilla and sour cream.
Combine the flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix into creamed ingredients until smooth.
In a bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
At high speed, gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar until mixture holds firm peaks.
Fold egg white mixture into the cake batter until well blended.
Pour 1/3 of the cake batter into a buttered 10-inch Bundt cake pan.
Knead 1 packet of chocolate until soft.
Snip off 1 corner.
Squeeze out chocolate onto cake batter in an irregular pattern.
Repeat with second packet of chocolate.
Top with remaining batter and chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
Turn onto serving plate. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: laulau
directions: Cut pork butt and butterfish into 8 pieces and salt it generously.
Wash taro leaves. Remove stem and large vein from each leaf.
Wrap one piece of meat into 2 to 3 taro leaves. Arrange 3 ti leaves on table, crossing each leaf and making a circle.
Place taro wrapped pork and butterfish in center of ti leaves, bringing ti leaf end up, and tie together tightly with string.
Cut excess ti leaf stalks.
Arrange on a rack of a large steam pot with a tight fitting cover.
Add water and steam for 4 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sau-egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned and drain.
In bowl toss sausage and bread cubes.
In another bowl beat eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Pour into sausage mixture; add cheese.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 12.

title: world famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients, mixing in one at a time. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes approximately 48 cookies.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry rice, onion, peppers and mushrooms in butter and brown. Turn heat down and add package of brown gravy and 2 cups of water; simmer.
Cook rice in 1 cup of water in 1 minute.
Cover and let set 5 minutes in 10-inch skillet.
Melt butter, slightly beaten egg, chopped onion and chopped pepper and brown slightly.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons soy sauce, 1/3 cup water and mushrooms if desired.

title: southern tea cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 1/2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: In baking dish layer potatoes and onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and milk; pour over potatoes and onions.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender and a little brown on top.

title: golden potato donuts
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Beat eggs; add sugar, mashed potatoes and bacon fat.
Beat well; add milk.
Do not beat.
Add dry ingredients and stir until flour disappears.
Set in refrigerator to chill.
Place 1/2 chilled dough on floured board. Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter.
Fry in deep fat at 350°.

title: biscuit burgers
directions: Shape sausage into 6 patties and broil 3 minutes to 6 minutes until well done turning once.
Add cheese and cook just until it melts.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix until dough forms ball. Shape into small balls, 1 teaspoon each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese with sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour and beat well.
Bake in tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cook meat (1/8-inch slices cut across grain) with oil in skillet.
Add garlic, salt, ginger and pepper.
Saute until garlic is golden.

Remove all from skillet. Add green peppers and onions to skillet. Cook for 3 minutes. Return meat to skillet. Add soy sauce, bouillon and cornstarch mixture. Add beef bouillon cube dissolved in 1/2 cup boiling water. May replace canned beef bouillon.
Simmer 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve over hot white rice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix both cans of corn, 2 tablespoons sugar and eggs together. Sprinkle remaining sugar over top and distribute pats of butter over top. Microwave or oven bake at 350° for
20 minutes or until firm.
Serve hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt paraffin in top of double boiler.
Add chocolate chips. When chocolate chips are melted, turn down heat, dip peanut butter balls into mixture with toothpicks and place on wire rack to drain.

title: salmon florentine
directions: Line bottom of casserole with spinach that has been thawed and well drained.
Saute mushrooms in a little butter and mix with salmon.
Put on top of spinach.
Make a thick cream sauce with butter, flour and the salmon liquid plus half and half, adding 1 cup of grated cheese.
Add a little Tabasco to sauce and salt, if needed.
Spread sauce over top of casserole.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top of sauce.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven until hot and bubbly, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mel's lasagna
directions: Brown meat in butter. Drain fat. Add garlic powder, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Boil, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
(Cook noodles, drain and rinse in cold water.) Mix soft cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add sauce. Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls. Add layer of cheeses.
Add layer of noodles.
Repeat layers until sauce is gone (approximately 3 layers).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll dough into small balls.
Roll each ball in granulated sugar; decorate each with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cold slaw - cucumber and onions
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over slaw.

title: egg strata
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 12 pan with broken up pieces of bread. Scramble the eggs with the rest of the ingredients and pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and flour in heavy saucepan or double boiler.
Add egg yolks and milk gradually to mix well and not lump up.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine; stir and mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and bake or cover with Cool Whip when cool.

title: prize winning chili
directions: Fry ground beef with onion until done.
Add chili beans, chili soup and tomato sauce.
Fill chili soup can with water and add to mixture.
Add brown sugar, cinnamon and cocoa.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer for at least 1/2 hour.
Cook spaghetti until done.
Drain.
Serve chili over spaghetti and top with Cheddar cheese to taste.

title: rum slush
directions: Bring tea to a boil with 6 cups water.
Let tea stand for several hours.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Freeze in large container.
Add 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: baked ham
directions: Cook ham as directed on can.
At least 30 minutes before done, score and spread with pineapple glaze.
Garnish with whole cloves, if desired.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Crust:
Toast oats in shallow pan at 350° for 10 minutes. Combine with sugar and butter.
Press 3/4 of the oat mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill.

title: favorite bean soup(high fiber)
directions: Combine all ingredients including liquid from beans.
Cover and simmer over medium heat 1 hour.
If desired, sprinkle with grated Parmesan or Romano cheese before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Soak raisins in water.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over other ingredients. Place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: snowy white fudge
directions: Melt butter;
brush
side
with melted butter.
Add milk and sugar; cook
over medium heat to boiling point.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and cook to soft ball stage, 12 to
15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add wafers, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla
and
nuts;
mix
well.
Pour
into
9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut when cooled.
Very good at Christmas.

title: slow cooker chicken
directions: The night before
or
early
in
the
morning,	combine frozen orange juice concentrate, salt and pepper with 1 cup of the water, the catsup, soy sauce, brown sugar, mustard, garlic salt and ginger.
Mix well and pour into a large bowl.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove bones and skin and break into small pieces.
Add mushroom and chicken soups and broth; mix well. Add stuffing mix.
Pour into greased casserole dish; top with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in a sheet pan. When cool, break apart or cut in small squares. Place in the bottom of a punch bowl. Pour crushed pineapple (do not drain) over cake. Mix pudding and let set until thickened. Pour over pineapple. Pour pie filling over pudding. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until firm. Any favorite pie filling or fresh fruit in season may be used. Half the recipe fills a large mixing bowl.

title: salmon dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Stir in soup and milk. Stir in salmon next and peas.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add ice cream and fresh strawberries.
Place in serving bowl.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Chill for 1 or 2 hours in refrigerator.
Take out roll; cut into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Sprinkle with water.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° on bottom shelf for 10 minutes, then on top shelf until cracked on the top, about 5 minutes more.

title: banana cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg.
Add rind and cranberries.
Stir in milk and banana.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours (test after 1 hour).

title: parmesan chicken sticks
directions: You will need ice cream sticks.

title: scripture holiday cake
directions: Proverbs 23:14 first clause.
Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and you will have a good cake.

title: crock-pot white beans
directions: Bring to boil on stove, then put them in your crock-pot on low heat.
Put lid on and forget them for 6 hours.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Place cooked, chopped chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Spread cream of celery soup, then layer 2 cans of mixed vegetables. Next, spread cream of mushroom soup and follow with cream of chicken soup.
Mix melted margarine and flour with whisk, then add milk.
Pour over top of dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Combine the 2nd list of ingredients in another mixing bowl. Add the dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into loaf.
Will make 3 large loaves or 6 to 8 mini loaves.
Bake in mini loaves about 45 minutes until done.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Put in a jar and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours until it thickens.
Serve on crackers.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon jug.
Fill remainder of jug with water.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes. Cut small slits in cake, then pour Coco Casa on cake.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook about 1 hour

title: pork chop meal
directions: Brown chops, remove from skillet.
Add onions and rice to drippings, stir until brown.
Dissolve chicken cube in hot water. Add to rice and onion.
Bring to a boil, stir in chopped apples. Pour into a baking dish, arrange pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Coat apple slices and arrange over pork chops.
Bake until tender.

title: dutch "brownies"
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Add flour.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325 for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and slivered almonds if desired.

title: heavenly caramels
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup, combine sugar, cream, syrup and butter.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Microwave on High 12 to 13 minutes or until mixture reaches 246°.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: bill and carolyn's egg and sausage souffle
directions: Mix all together and cover.
Put into refrigerator overnight. Heat oven to 350°.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.
Cut into squares.

title: danish red berry pudding
directions: Combine berries in a food processor or blender and blend until pureed.
Strain the berry mixture to remove the seeds.
Combine the berries with 1 cup water in a medium-size saucepan.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine crab, green onions, celery, cream cheese and mayo. Mix well. In separate bowl, dissolve lemon juice in the Knox gelatine. In a small saucepan, heat soup in condensed form until hot. Remove from heat. Add Knox and stir together. Mix all ingredients together. Pour in a mold to set for 24
hours. Serve with crackers or bread.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Broil the spareribs in broiler until golden brown on both sides.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Boil combined ingredients for 10 minutes in an uncovered saucepan.
Place spareribs in an uncovered roaster and pour part of the sauce over them.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, basting every 10 minutes with the boiling hot sauce.

title: kraft macaroni dinner
directions: Cook macaroni with salt.
Drain after it's done and set aside. Add 1 tablespoon margarine.
Stir in hot macaroni.
Stir once in a while to keep from being lumpy.
Cook hamburger meat with salt to taste.
When done, cook chopped pepper and onion until tender. Now add tomato sauce, water, garlic powder, chili powder and black pepper.
Cook 10 minutes on low fire.
Add cheese.
Stir with fork.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: amish dressing
directions: Brown bread in 1/2 stick oleo, turn often.
Remove from heat. Beat eggs, add milk, salt and pepper to taste and mix together. Melt other 1/2 stick in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Meanwhile, mix egg mixture with carrots, celery, potatoes, chicken, parsley and milk.
Stir in bread crumbs and pour over oleo in baking dish. Bake at 350° until browned all around.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Put into 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (uncovered).

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or thaw hash browns before mixing together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green olivada (olive spread)
directions: Combine all ingredients except olive oil in food processor fitted with metal blade.
Process until coarsely chopped, scraping down sides of bowl once or twice.
Add oil in a thin stream with motor running and continue processing until mixture is a coarse puree.
Store the olivada in a covered container in the refrigerator for at least 3 days, or up to 2
weeks, before serving.
Remove to room temperature at least 30 minutes before serving with thinly sliced Italian bread or crackers.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until well mixed. This will make enough chicken salad to make 8 full sandwiches.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, milk, eggs, 1/2 cup margarine and coconut.
Add nuts, brown sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and flour together.
Pour over the top of the other ingredients. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot dog and cheese crescents
directions: Split hot dogs to within 1/2-inch of ends. Insert 3 strips cheese into each slit. Separate dough in 8 triangles.
Wrap dough over wieners, keeping cheese side up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until crescent is golden brown.

title: white fluffy frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler; place over boiling water.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Remove from boiling water; add vanilla.

title: quick meatless stew(serves four)
directions: *Optional: Of course other vegetables can be added, if desired.

title: pumpkin spice cake(microwave)
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Microwave for 10 minutes at 50% power and 5 to 6 minutes at 100% power.
Cover with 1 sheet of paper towel.
This will absorb the excess moisture.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: tall timbers pancakes
directions: With a whisk, mix egg, oil, milk, water and vanilla in a bowl. In another bowl mix pancake mix, sugar and baking powder. Gradually add dry ingredients to liquid mixture, mixing well with a whisk.
Cook pancakes on slightly greased griddle, using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Dice onion.
Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients, except noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and continue baking long enough for cheese to melt.

title: cucumber pickles(3 day pickles)
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers 1/2 inch thick.
Mix lime in 1 gallon of cold water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand in covered water 24 hours.
Wash pickles in cold water twice and soak in ice clear water 4 hours.
Drain.

title: blueberry loaf cake(it has excellent texture and contains no fat)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Add beaten egg until
thick.
Add orange rind.
Stir in orange juice. Add to
dry
ingredients.
Add
blueberries
and
mix lightly. Turn into greased loaf
pan
x
x 2 1/2-inches. Bake at
for
about 50 minutes until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Turn out on wire rack and cool.
Store in tightly
covered
container
several hours or overnight to ripen before slicing.

title: scratch waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks in small bowl.
Beat in milk and cooking oil. In large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add egg mixture to flour and stir until well blended, but slightly lumpy.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks.
Carefully fold egg whites into flour mixture.
Pour batter into greased waffle iron.
Can be frozen and popped into toaster for quick breakfast.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 3 1/2 cups.
Bring juice mixture and sugar to a boil.
Add cranberries and cook 7 to 10 minutes or until berries pop.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in grapes, pecans and pineapple.
Pour into lightly oiled 8 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
The last 15 minutes, sprinkle corn flake crumbs over the top.

title: stain removal
directions: Put the hot water in a plastic bucket (do not use metal bucket).
Mix all ingredients; stir well.
Put stain removal on a 100% cotton white garment.
Soak for 30 minutes, then wash as usual.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat cherries and their juice to boiling.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir.
Add pineapple, juice and all.
Pour Coke and nuts.
Pour into oiled 6-cup mold.
Let cool; then refrigerate at least 2 hours or until set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in broth and heat the water and add to gelatin.
Add all other ingredients and put in an oiled mold.

title: lamb stew
directions: Cut lamb into 1-inch cubes.
Brown lamb, onion and garlic in olive oil in a large skillet or saucepan.
Drain off excess fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and boil gently covered, 1 hour or until lamb is tender.
(Add more water during cooking, if necessary.)
Serve with rice.
Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and bake 15 minutes in lightly greased muffin pans.
(Jalapeno peppers may be left out for those who cannot "take the heat".)

title: wonderful vegetable dip
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients and chill.

title: honey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: buttery brie with walnuts
directions: Saute shelled chopped walnuts in butter in a skillet over medium heat and set aside.
Place a wheel of Brie with top crust removed into medium oven and heat until inside is very soft (approximately 10 minutes).
Pour walnuts in butter over the Brie and place on serving dish.
Serve hot with crackers.
The nuts and butter will mingle with the soft cheese, creating a unique and interesting flavor.

title: sand tarts
directions: Heat 2-inches of water in double boiler.
Turn off.
Over double boiler, beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar and beat 10 minutes.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls and bake in 200° oven for 6 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix and butter; spread mix in bottom of casserole.
Add vegetable mixture.
Put a little stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple; add enough water to syrup to make 1 1/3 cups liquid.
In a 10-inch skillet that can go into the oven, melt the butter.
Remove from heat and sprinkle with the brown sugar.
Arrange 8 slices of pineapple on the sugar; let stand.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: Prepare ground beef with directions on back of the taco seasoning package.
Spread sour cream in bottom of a round tray with 1 or 2-inch sides.
Spread ground beef over sour cream in a thin layer, leaving one-inch of sour cream showing all around.
Put refried beans in a layer over ground beef.
Sprinkle tomato pieces over refried beans.
Add salsa over tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese as next layer.
Sprinkle onion and green pepper over the top.
Dip tortilla chips.

title: stir-fried green beans
directions: Cut beans into 2-inch pieces.
Wash and dry well.
Soak mushrooms in boiling water for 15 minutes; squeeze out water. Slice thinly.
Stir-fry garlic in oil for 30 seconds.
Add beans and mushrooms, stir-fry until beans turn a darker green. Add sherry, soy sauce and sugar; cook, covered, for 2 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in broth and pour over beans.
Stir-fry until sauce thickens.

title: estelle's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form a loaf on a large sheet of heavy-duty foil, bringing sides of foil up to make a fold.
Seal edges and put in a pan or on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Last 10 minutes, open foil to brown meat loaf.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: garlic chicken with pasta
directions: Chicken and vegetables can be cut up night before.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla in bowl. Beat thoroughly.
Add flour, salt and baking soda, mixing well. Blend in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange and red onion salad
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar until dissolved.
Whisk in oil. Toss onions, oil and lettuce together.
Toss with enough dressing to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and score cucumbers.
Slice into thin rounds and put into nonmetallic bowl.

title: glazed winter squash
directions: Peel squash and cut in 1-inch cubes. Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well.
Place cubes of squash in shallow well-greased baking dish.
Pour other ingredients over squash.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.
Baste several times during baking time.

title: minestrone
directions: Brown bacon.
Add next 10 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add green beans, peas and spaghetti and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Have the last 4 ingredients ready for use, cook noodles according to package direction.
Drain noodles.
In large bowl, toss noodles with Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
In serving platter, spoon sauce to cover bottom.
Layer 1/2 noodle mixture, then more sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand or Eagle Brand low-fat, ReaLemon and food coloring if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell; bake 30 minutes.
Cool. Chill; spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Prep.
Time:
10 minutes.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Cream Jell-O powder with cream cheese.
Blend mayo.
Add hot water and beat with electric mixer.
Mix in pineapple and chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt stick of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear bread into cubes and place in pan.
Sprinkle with diced ham and grated Cheddar cheese.
Crack eggs into bowl, beat until foamy, add salt, pepper and milk.
Mix well and pour over bread, ham and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour.

title: christmas congealed salad
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve cherry gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Combine all ingredients; congeal.
Yields 8 servings.

title: bakeless oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and peanut butter; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat and mix with oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop on waxed paper with teaspoon. Cool.

title: grilled chicken sauce
directions: Melt margarine and mix in other ingredients.
Brush on chicken as you grill.

title: mexican chicken casserole(direct from corpus christi, tx)
directions: Cook chicken and noodles.
Chop up chicken and spread in a 9x13-inch casserole.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate; remove and cool.
Brew coffee and dissolve gelatin.
Add rum and vanilla.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup of sugar until light and thick.
Beat in chocolate and stir in coffee mixture.
Beat egg whites until foamy and doubled in volume.

Add remaining 1/4 cup of sugar slowly until mixture holds firm peaks. Beat about 1/4 of the meringue mixture into chocolate mixture. Fold in beaten cream and meringue until there are no more streaks. Chill 2 hours in freezer.

title: mee mee's banana pudding
directions: Put milk on low heat and bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Add egg mixture to milk and bring to a boil again.
Add vanilla last.
Layer sliced bananas and wafers on bottom of dish.
Pour pudding over top of layer and alternate with bananas and wafers until all is used.
Let cool.

title: sour cream poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a buttered Bundt or tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serves 12.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: In a saucepan, heat undiluted cream of mushroom soup until hot.
Remove from heat and add gelatin and water mixture.
Allow to cool slightly.
Mix softened cream cheese and mayonnaise well and add to saucepan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour into greased mold.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
