Unmold to plate and serve with assorted crackers.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Cream together flour, margarine and pecans.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream together sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Spread pie filling on top.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice enough apples to fill medium pan within 1 inch of top.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Mix in flour sifter the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and butter.
Blend a little cinnamon with the flour mixture.
Spread mixture over top of apples and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gumbo or alligator tails and crocodile tonsils
directions: Heat butter or oil in skillet.
Add chopped onion and saute until just soft.
Add sliced okra and saute until barely done. Add chunked tomatoes and cook only until tomatoes are hot through. Season with salt and pepper.

title: delicious oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
In large mixer bowl, combine oats, oat bran, flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and sugar.

title: soft dropped sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine in large bowl.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in flour, soda and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar before putting in oven.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp and artichoke soup
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, saving 1/2 cup liquid.
Heat liquid and dissolve chicken bouillon cube in it.
Set aside.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter, stirring, until tender.
Stir in flour and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly and light brown.
Gradually stir in bouillon mixture, wine and milk.
Cook until mixture thickens and boils.
Add shrimp, artichoke and seasonings.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Yields 6 servings.
Cafe Bon Appetit.

title: orange and pineapple salad
directions: Arrange the crisp lettuce.
Cut the oranges in sections.
If you skin the orange with a very sharp knife and cut away the pith, you can then cut each section of orange without using the skin. Arrange on the lettuce.
Serve with French dressing.
Add diced pineapple and finely chopped egg white to garnish.

title: layered pistachio dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix, brown sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes. Cool.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash 2 cups bean mix.
Place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water, about 2 inches above beans; let soak overnight. Drain.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil. Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 8 cups.
Freezes well.

title: baked cheese spread
directions: Mix enough mayonnaise to blend cheese & onion together. Place ingredients into a casserole dish & bake until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients and stir well.
Can also be frozen in a 9 x 13-inch pan and served in a solid form.
Can also be frozen in cupcake papers for individual servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice berries into bottom of pie shell.
Heat til thickened: sugar, water, and cornstarch then remove from heat and add jello. Pour into pie crust.
Cool 2 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and Crisco. Mix with remaining ingredients and pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° or 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean. DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece of biscuit into the melted butter and then into the cinnamon and sugar which have been mixed together.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chile verde
directions: Boil jalapeno, yellow onion, garlic and tomatillos until tender.
Blend in blender to make a sauce.

title: steelhead trout in tomato-basil-butter sauce
directions: Melt 1 1/2 teaspoons butter in small skillet.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Stir often.
Cook until liquid evaporates and mixture thickens.
Add 1/4 cup butter and garlic.
Stir over medium heat until mixture becomes sauce type consistency.
Stir in basil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place fillets in cooking dish.
Spoon tomato mixture over fillets.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the oil and sugar well. Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Oil and flour a Bundt pan and bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven or in muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in cherry pie filling. Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and chill until partially set.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cocoa and cake mix together.
Add buttermilk, eggs, butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well.
Add soda and vinegar.
Mix well.
Next grease and flour 3 layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut bonbon
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water in pan.
Stir until it boils.
Wash down sides of pan with a buttered cloth dipped in cold water.
Boil until a soft ball forms.
Take from heat; add coconut and butter. Stir just enough to mix.
Pour in buttered pan.
When cold, make into balls.
Lay on wax paper after dipping in melted chocolate. May also roll in sugar.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt butter and oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Stir.
Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes or until pink.

title: inside-out cake
directions: Grease and flour a bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients, pour in pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
You can mix and match cake mix and icing flavors.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Stir in sugar; add flour and nutmeg. Mix together.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into 9-inch uncooked crust. Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cottage fruit salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese until it is all colored. Add drained fruit cocktail.
Stir in Cool Whip to blend.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding; fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan with graham crackers.
Alternate 2 layers each of pudding, then crackers.
Top with topping.

title: spinach strawberry salad
directions: In a mixer or blender, mix first 4 ingredients, add oil slowly.
Add poppy seeds.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1 package strawberry jello and cool.
Slice 1 pint strawberries for each pie.
Makes 2 pies.
Cover with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: grilled steak with mustard marinade
directions: Place the steak in a large glass or ceramic dish.
In a medium bowl, whisk the remaining ingredients together.
Pour over the meat; coat both sides.
Cover and allow to marinate at room temperature for 1 hour or in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Preheat an outdoor grill or a broiler.
Remove the steak from the marinade and grill for 5 minutes on each side or until cooked to the desired doneness, basting occasionally with the marinade. Serve immediately, sliced on the bias.
Serves 8.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand.
Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Beat the egg and add to yeast and water.
Add shortening to flour and stir in yeast mixture until thoroughly mixed.
Cover with a damp cloth or plastic cover and put in refrigerator.
Remove from refrigerator 2 hours before serving time and make into desired shapes.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Can be made up the day before.

title: poppy bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes two loaves.

title: upside-down cake gets new twist
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, combine dry frosting and cinnamon; reserve 1 cup for topping.
To the frosting mix in pan, add pineapple and egg yolks.
Stir well to blend and spread evenly over bottom of pan.
In large mixer bowl, combine dry cake mix, egg whites and water.
Blend until moistened.
Beat as directed on cake package.
Spread batter over pineapple mixture.
Cut butter into thin slices over batter. Sprinkle reserved frosting mix over butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cool. Store in refrigerator.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place 4 chicken breasts (halved and boned, 8 fillets) in mayonnaise coated casserole.
Cover with slices of Swiss cheese. Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup with 1/4 cup chicken broth; pour over chicken and cheese.
Cover top with bread crumbs or croutons and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick oleo, set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick oleo.
Add eggs.
Alternate flour, soda and buttermilk. Add melted candy, oleo and pecans; blend together.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour or tested done.
Frost with Milky Way Icing.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix all other ingredients.
Put in layers in mixing bowl.
Let marinate overnight out of refrigerator.
Chill before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except beans and bacon.
When mixed well add 2 cans of beans and lay bacon strips on top of beans.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or longer or until not so soupy at 325°.

title: easter eggs
directions: Beat cream cheese, vanilla, milk and margarine at high speed until creamy.
Add powdered sugar.
Shape and dip into melted chocolate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello as per package directions and cool.
Set aside. Chop the oranges, apples and cranberries in the food processor. Stir into the cooled jello.
Stir in the chopped celery. Refrigerate to set.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook crust for 20 minutes (no longer).
Be sure to cool completely.

title: white bread
directions: Combine the warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar in a small bowl. Add yeast and stir to mix. Set aside until mixture becomes bubbly. In a large bowl, combine the remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar, salt, milk, and melted shortening. Mix well.

Add 1 cup of the flour and the yeast mixture. Mix well. Add another cup of flour and whisk until the mixture is smooth. This can be done with an electric mixer. Continue adding the flour until dough is moderately stiff. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead until the dough is smooth and elastic. The kneading time should be 8 to 10 minutes. Shape into a ball.

Place in a lightly oiled bowl. Turn once to oil all surfaces. Cover the bowl with a damp dish towel. Let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk. This should take about an hour. Punch dough down. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface. Divide into two portions.
Shape each into a ball.

Cover with the towel and let dough rest for 10 minutes. Grease two 9x5x3 inch loaf pans. Shape each portion of dough into a loaf. This can be done by simply pulling the dough into a loaf shape and tucking the edges under. Place the loaves into the prepared pans.
Cover with the damp towel.
Let rise in a warm place until the dough rises above the top of the pan.
This should take 40 to 50 minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix together jello, 2 cups boiling water, 1 cup pineapple and apricot juice, mixed.
Combine apricots, pineapple and marshmallows and add to jello mixture after it is thick.
Let set firmly.

title: feetsie's dressing for tossed salad
directions: Stir well all ingredients and cover for 2 to 3 hours.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred the cabbage.
Combine the mayonnaise, lemon juice and ginger and mix with cabbage.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: special macaroni salad(low calorie)
directions: Put milk and water in nonstick saucepan.
Stir in mustard, lemon juice, oil and macaroni.
Cook over low flame, stirring, until liquid begins to simmer.
Turn burner very low and cover pan.
Stir frequently for 25 minutes.
If mixture gets too thick, add a little water.
After 25 minutes, cover and refrigerate until cool.
Stir slightly with spoon to restore creamy texture.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill before serving. One serving equals 120 calories.

title: caramel-chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of the milk in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Keep mixture warm over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Mix dry cake mix, margarine, remaining milk and the pecans.
Spread half of the dough in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes; remove from oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour and banana; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Add pecans after ingredients are mixed well.
Roll dough into small balls; bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes.
Roll hot cookies in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Prepare cake according to instructions on box.
Take lid off marshmallow cream.
Heat for 20 seconds in microwave oven.
Punch holes in baked sheet cake with wooden spoon handle.
Heat milk, sugar, coconut and marshmallow cream to boiling point.
Pour over hot cake.
When cake cools, top with Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken, vegetables, soup and milk.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: antipasto salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together cooking oil, vinegar, garlic, basil, salt and pepper.
Add warm noodles and Parmesan cheese. Toss to coat well. Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Add broccoli, pepperoni and tomatoes. Toss until well mixed. Serve on lettuce lined platter. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. If desired, garnish with red onion rings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie(serves 8)
directions: In a mixing bowl, add milk and strawberries; blend 15 seconds. Fold in Cool Whip, then pour into pie crusts.
Use the plastic top from the crust to make lid for pies; crimp down the sides. Place in freezer for about 2 hours.

title: alice lee's egg custard pie(delicious)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt together.
Add 3 eggs and beat 2 minutes, then add 3 more eggs and beat 2 minutes, adding flavoring and milk.
This recipe is for one 9-inch pie.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Do not prick crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then at 300° for 30 minutes or longer, perhaps an hour.

title: peanut butter chocolate stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, sugar and egg in medium bowl until blended and smooth.
Shape into 48 balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheets. Press a chocolate star onto top of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Place peeled and cubed potatoes in large pot. Cover with water. Cook until fork-tender. Do not drain. Cook bacon while potatoes are cooking. Drain and crumble. Set aside. When potatoes are tender, add butter, salt and pepper to taste and cream. Cook until bubbly. Thicken with cornstarch and add bacon. Cook until all flavors are combined. Enjoy!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring kraut to a boil.
Add sugar.
Cool.
Pour over the remaining ingredients.
Toss and chill.

title: spam spread
directions: Mince Spam in medium-size bowl; add cream cheese.
Mash with fork.
Add minced green onion tops, garlic and mayonnaise.
Mix well to blend.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: cent-saving apricot short ribs
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper bag; shake short ribs in seasoned flour until coated.
(Reserve remaining seasoned flour.)
Brown meat in hot oil in Dutch oven.
Remove meat and saute onion in drippings until lightly browned.
Return meat to Dutch oven and add bouillon cubes, 2 cups water, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and spices.
Bring to boil, cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 hour and 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove short ribs to serving plate; keep warm.
Pour cooking liquid into quart measure; skim off fat.
If necessary, add water to make 3 cups liquid; return to Dutch oven.
Blend 1/4 cup of the seasoned flour with 1/3 cup water; stir into Dutch oven.
Cook, stirring constantly, until gravy boils, about 1 minute.
Add fruit and salt to taste.
Arrange noodles or rice around meat on serving platter. Spoon the fruit and part of the gravy over the meat and noodles or rice.
Serve remainder in bowl.

title: corn and spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir and bake for 30 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: filled tomatoes
directions: Take pulp out of tomatoes.
Fill with bread filling made with the listed ingredients.
Bake at 375° until bread is browned.

title: fruit and cookie salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip and drained oranges.
Crush the cookies and add just before serving.

title: corn and potato casserole
directions: Cook potato.
Mix all the other ingredients.
Bake in the oven at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: jezebel
directions: Spread cream cheese on crackers and then put a bit of Jezebel on top of cream cheese.

title: ambrosia dip
directions: In a large bowl place all ingredients and beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Makes approximately 22 ounces.
Serve with Jell-O mold or fresh fruit.

title: eve's white cake for company
directions: Mix and bake the cake according to directions in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
While the cake is baking, heat the milk and sugar to boiling; stir to dissolve.
Five minutes before cake is done, remove from the oven.
Poke holes all over the top with a fork. Pour the hot sugar and milk mixture over the top.
Return to the oven for 5 more minutes.
Once cool, frost the cake with Cool Whip topping.
Sprinkle with coconut and/or chopped nuts.
Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: smothered steak
directions: Mix egg and milk; beat well with fork.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and seasoned salt in separate bowl.
Cut round steak into serving sizes; dip each piece in egg mixture, then into flour mixture.
Brown steak in oil on top of stove.
When all pieces of steak are browned, layer steak in ovenproof pan.
Mix soups and mushrooms; pour over steak and add enough milk to make mixture thin.
Cover and bake in hot oven until mixture is hot and bubbly and steak is tender, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: belgium waffle
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored; add milk.
Add melted butter alternately with sifted ingredients.
Fold in well beaten egg whites (not too dry).
Bake on hot waffle iron.
Top with whipped cream and sliced, sweetened strawberries.
Makes 6 to 8 waffles.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and syrup and bring to boil for 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda; stir well.

title: brunch potato casserole
directions: Saute all ingredients (except beans) in margarine for 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in beans and heat.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You may top with low-fat shredded cheese and broil until melted.

title: apple-pumpkin pie
directions: Make pie dough and place in pie pan.
Flute outer edge.
Line pie shell with apple pie mixture.
Mix pumpkin mix with rest of ingredients as you would for regular pumpkin mix.
Pour on top of apple pie mix in pie shell until pie reaches rim of crust.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 70 minutes.
A butter knife should be stuck in center of pie and come out clean to be considered done.
Let cool before serving with whip cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs, butter, vanilla and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a 1-inch ball.
Push down with glass that has been dipped in sugar (first press on dough, then in sugar and press on top of cookies to flatten slightly).
May sprinkle with additional sugar, if desired.
Bake 2 inches apart for 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 dozen 4-inch cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add peppers, onions, chili powder, pepper, salt, tomatoes and shortening.
Pour into casserole dish and add rice.
Stir.
Put in oven for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Thaw potatoes; mix with oleo, salt, pepper, onion, soup and sour cream.
Add cheese.
Place in casserole; cover with corn flake crumbs, mixed with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all in a blender.

title: aunt jo's cheese cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pat into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons vanilla and eggs, added 1 at a time, and mixed well after each egg.
Pour onto cooled graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Allow to set 10 minutes.
Combine sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and pour onto warm cheese cake, after it has cooled 10 minutes and bake for an additional 10 minutes.
Let cool completely and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add milk, egg and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple-cheese bake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserving juice.
Set aside.
Combine egg and sugar in saucepan, beating until foamy.
Add flour and juice, stirring until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese on top. Saute crushed Ritz crackers and 1/2 cup melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: grilled baked orange roughy
directions: Place a large sheet of aluminum foil (twice the size of what is needed to hold fish).
Brush a little of the butter over the foil. Place fish in center of foil and brush remaining butter over fish. Squeeze lemon over fish.
Sprinkle seasonings over fish.
Fold edges up and over to seal; set aside.
Preheat grill on medium for 10 minutes, then turn to low.
Place foil packet on cooking grid. Close lid and grill 8 to 10 minutes, turning after 5 minutes until fish flakes when tested with fork.

title: fresh cranberry nut cake
directions: Let the water, chopped cranberries, sugar and pecans or walnuts stand about 6 hours to form juice.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Mix together hot applesauce, shortening and sugar.
Heat over low heat until shortening is melted (best to let stand overnight). Sift together all dry ingredients; add to applesauce mixture. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300° to 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken provencale
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts and dip in flour.
Saute in olive oil until browned.
Add tomatoes, garlic, oregano and wine. Cook covered over medium heat for 25 minutes.
Add mushrooms. Cook for 15 minutes more.
Serve over white rice or pasta.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add macaroni and cheese.
Boil for 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Then add milk and water.

title: fish stew
directions: Partially cook the elbow macaroni; drain.
Cook the spinach and mixed vegetables until nearly done, reserving the liquids. Saute the onion and celery.
Add the flaked fish, spices and the rest of the ingredients.
Heat through.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and reserve liquid.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in orange rind.
Pour pineapple juice in 2 cup measuring cup, add lemon juice and enough cold water to make 2 cups.
Stir into jello mix.
Chill for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until thick as egg whites (unbeaten).
Fold in berries, celery, walnuts and pineapple.
Pour into a lightly oiled 2-quart fluted ring mold or crown.
Chill at least 24 hours.
Line a round platter with lettuce.
Then invert salad onto lettuce.
Cut into small pieces. Serves 16.

title: marbled squares
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Cream together next 5 ingredients.
Put eggs into creamed mixture.
Put mixture into greased 11 x 17-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Place in hot oven on 320° for 1 minute.
Remove from oven and run knife through melted chips and make swirls.
Return to oven and cook 18 minutes more.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; boil over low heat, stir until thick, then add the butter and beat with spoon until smooth.
Pour into baked 8 or 9-inch pie shell.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: clam balls
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Roll into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil until cooked.
Drain when done. Place in a bowl while still hot.
Add onions, celery and salad dressing; mix together.
Sprinkle oregano leaves on top.
Mix again.
Cover it with wrap.
Refrigerate until cool.
Make the day before, it tastes better.

title: gummies
directions: Mix well.
Spread in a sheet cake pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: quick curry dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a jar with lid.
Stir well.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt brown sugar and shortening in top part of double boiler. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to this the shortening and sugar mixture, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Next, add chocolate bits and nuts.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar free maple cookies(low-fat for diabetics)
directions: Combine margarine, sour cream, apple, eggs, maple flavoring and vanilla; mix well. Add dry ingredients. Drop by tablespoon on baking sheets sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake at 375° for 9 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 30 to 35 soft cookies. Store in airtight container.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; mix with crumbs and pat out in an 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: a.1.  beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Take beef from skillet.
Add to the same skillet, the remaining margarine and cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
Return meat to skillet; add water and steak sauce; heat to a boil.
Reduce to low.
Simmer 50 to 60 minutes until tender.
Stir in sour cream and serve over noodles.

title: tangy orange and fruit brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray or solid shortening.
In a large bowl, combine brownie mix, orange peel, orange juice and egg whites; stir 75 strokes by hand.
Stir in fruit bits.
Spread in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, egg yolks, butter, water and flour.
Cook until thick.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: powerhouse cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients.
Batter will be thick and difficult to work with. Best method is to butter hands and work batter until it is well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for about 18 minutes or until brown.
Makes 15 dozen cookies.

title: date - pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and add eggs.
Add all dry ingredients. Chill.
Roll dough out like a jelly-roll.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat until cheese is smooth.
Add orange juice, juice from 1 can of oranges and Mandarin oranges.
Cool until firm.

title: egg and ham casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake casserole for about 50 minutes or until lightly browned around edges and set in center.

title: parfait punch
directions: Boil together until dissolved the sugar and water.

Add bananas, orange juice, lemons, strawberries and pineapple juice. Mix together and freeze at least 24 hours. When ready to serve, add 3 (16 ounce) bottles 7-Up to each 1/2 gallon of unthawed punch.
Pour 7-Up over punch. Mix about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: elsie's salad
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients.
Combine pepper, carrot and onion and beans.
Pour vinegar and oil mixture over vegetables.
Stir and chill for 24 hours.

title: honey roasted potatoes
directions: Add potatoes to a pan of cold water and bring to a boil. Then drain immediately. Place potatoes in baking dish with oil and butter; sprinkle with salt. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Baste with honey. Bake another 20 minutes more. Serve.

title: brazilian prestigio
directions: In pot over medium heat, stir in condensed milk and grated coconut.
Dissolve flour in milk.
Add to pot, stirring always until thickened.
Pour in shallow Pyrex plate, let cool for 15 minutes.
On the side, prepare package of chocolate pudding.
Then pour on top of coconut mix.
Put in refrigerator.

title: famous corn
directions: Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut pillows
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, margarine and sugars.
Mix at high speed until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Add flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla and eggs to mixture; beat until blended.
With a spoon, stir in the chopped peanuts.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip fresh fruits in dip.

title: homemade peanut butter eggs
directions: Cook sugar, water, syrup and salt. Boil 3 minutes. Beat egg whites until stiff. In large bowl, combine cooked ingredients and beaten egg whites, then peanut butter. Mix thoroughly. Form into eggs and lay on wax paper. In double boiler, melt about 1 pound chocolate. Put chocolate on eggs. Delicious!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Put halves of eggplant in salt water and boil until tender. Remove halves and take out pulp, leaving each shell clean.
Handle carefully.
Cool.
In skillet with small amount oil, brown onion and add ground beef; cook until done.
Chop eggplant pulp fine and add to meat and seasoning.
Add egg and mix well.
Lay the eggplant shells in a greased baking dish and top with meat mixture.
Cover with crushed cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: green pizza
directions: Mix pizza dough recipe according to directions.
Saute garlic and herbs in olive oil and butter until garlic is soft.
Add chicken broth and cornstarch, stirring until thickened.
Cover pizza dough with this mixture, then add layer of artichokes, ham, onions and cheese and sprinkle olives on top.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage marinara
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Spread 3 cups cabbage in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture and sprinkle with remaining 3 cups cabbage.
Pour undiluted soup over top.

title: pecan finger cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add salt, vanilla, water, flour and pecans.
Take teaspoon of dough; roll into oblong shape.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Put beef in pan with cut up vegetables; add tomato sauce until almost everything is covered.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium-high heat until tender.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix shortening and add other ingredients.
Spread in buttered pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer for 5 minutes.
Press crescent roll dough onto bottom
and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan; press edges together	to seal.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 375°
for
10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover with meat	mixture; top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Top with
remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: party salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling; dissolve gelatin and cream cheese in hot mixture.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients, chill until firm.
Yield 8-10 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the 1 cup sugar, flour and cocoa together first.
Beat egg yolks next and add them.
Then add can milk and vanilla.
Cook this 5 to 8 minutes on high heat, stirring all the time it is cooking.
It will burn easily.
After it thickens, pour into baked pie shell.	Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add the sugar.
Spread on top of pie and bake in oven (high) until brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion and green pepper gently in margarine.
Add carrots, salt and water to cover (2 cups water).
Simmer gently.
Add potatoes and simmer gently.
Add green beans, continue to simmer. When vegetables are tender, add milk and cheese, but under no circumstances allow soup to boil after adding milk and cheese. Serve when cheese is melted.
Keep enough water on vegetables while cooking to just barely keep them covered.
(I add the third cup of water with the green beans.)

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: "special" german chocolate cake
directions: Layer pecans and thawed coconut in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to instructions on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together. Spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat and form into patties. Brown patties in pan with oil. Add soup and 1/2 to 1 soup can of water. Add potatoes and carrots. Cover and cook 30 minutes on medium heat or until carrots and potatoes are done.

title: foil baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) in a mixing bowl; blend well.
Place chicken in a baking dish or foil pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake 40 to 55 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Cook ground turkey; drain.
Add taco seasoning package and stir.
Add refried beans and stir.
Let simmer.
Cube 1/2 block Velveeta cheese and put in microwave to melt.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes before melting.
Put turkey mix in glass serving dish.
Pour melted cheese/tomatoes over top.
Sprinkle with peppers.
Layer with sour cream and dap on 4 or 5 tablespoons guacamole.
Sprinkle black olives and green onions.
Serve with chips.
Twenty minutes prep time.

title: bacon and shrimp appetizers
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Cut bacon in fours.
Wrap bacon around shrimp and secure with a toothpick.
Put shrimp in a Tupperware container and pour teriyaki sauce over shrimp.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lasagna with shrimp
directions: Cook lasagna al dente (not quite done) according to package directions; plunge into cold water.
Drain well.
Reserve.
Spread out on waxed paper.

title: banana split salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk in bowl.
Beat well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Store in a jar with a tight lid.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add cornmeal and salt slowly.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Cool slightly.
Add egg yolks one at at time and beat after each addition.
Beat in baking powder.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for about 35 minutes or until firm and crust is brown. Serve with whipped butter.
Good with ham or chicken and salad.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl in order in which given. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well just before serving.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Rinse and drain blueberries.
Put into bowl and add sugar, flour, salt and lemon peel; toss lightly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Drizzle lemon juice over filling.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Prick top crust with fork. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, slice and place apples in a pie pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
In a separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture over mounded apple slices.
Bake 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandma verna's baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: our favorite cookies
directions: Mix
sugars,
eggs,
butter and vanilla together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to sugar mixture.
Stir well until
dough
is
stiff
enough to drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie
sheet and press flat.
Bake at 350° until the cookies are light brown.

title: monkey bread(yields 10 servings)
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Toss into mixing bowl.
Add the next 3 ingredients and toss.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook hamburger; drain off grease.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: "venus de milo" minestrone soup
directions: In large pot, brown hamburger.
Add chicken broth, water, soup mix and celery.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes and frozen mixed vegetables; boil 15 minutes.
Add pasta and boil until pasta is done.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top when served.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: In blender, place all ingredients, except chicken pieces. Blend until pureed.
Place chicken in glass or non-metal pan.
Pour garlic mixture over and turn chicken pieces to coat.
Pierce all over with fork.
Marinate in refrigerator for at least one hour or up to four hours.
Grill over medium-high heat or broil for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and thaw crab meat.
Combine all ingredients and stir.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Serve warm with chips or crackers.

title: brats 'n' beer
directions: Grill or pan-fry the brats until brown.
Bring the beer and onion to a boil in an electric skillet or crock-pot.
Put the brats into the beer-onion soup and simmer for at least 15 minutes or continue on low heat until ready to serve.
Serve with mashed potatoes and sauerkraut with brown sugar.
Serves six.

title: banana split brownie
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed. Let cool. Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and crushed pineapple, slightly drained. Pour over brownie. Cut up bananas over that layer. Cover with Cool Whip. Cut up strawberries on top. Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Keep in refrigerator.

title: easy scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook cracker crumbs in margarine until lightly browned.
Drain tomatoes.
Mix 1/2 cup juice from tomatoes, then drained tomatoes and seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 21 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add and mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325 degrees for 2 hours.
Good served with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Drain strawberries.
Mix strawberries and whipped cream together.
Cut frozen cake in half.
Cut halves in half again.

title: jewish bundt cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; add oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar and egg mixture and beat.
Add peeled and sliced apples. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix the oleo and 1 1/4 cups sugar well. Add the eggs, sour cream, flour, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla. Put half the mixture in angel food pan. Mix the ground nuts, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar together in separate small bowl. Put half of nut mixture over cake in pan. Fill pan with rest of batter and cover with the remaining nut mixture. Start this in a cold oven and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Soften butter, mix sugar and flour until it round yellow ball. Line pan with wax paper and pat into pan, prick with fork. Bake till golden brown at 350°, it will brown around the edges, watch, it will burn quickly. Cool on a rack. Cut into squares. Size of pan determines the thickness of the squares.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook
in
Dutch
oven
or
6 quart pot.
Saute onion in Promise.
Add
beef and cook on medium heat until most of pink is gone.
Add	tomatoes,
carrots
and potatoes, bay leaf and bouillon
cube.
Bring
to	boil and then reduce to simmer for approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add pepper
and
check
for salt.
Add if necessary.
Stew is even better the second day.
Good served with garlic bread.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put oyster crackers. Mix oil, dill weed, garlic powder and Ranch dressing in bowl. Pour over crackers. Put lid on bowl and shake. Let stand for 1 hour, shaking several times.

title: yogurt popsicle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not add water to orange juice.
Pour into popsicle molds and freeze until firm.
A good snack for children.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Pour cereal and stir until coated.
Cool.

title: special biscuit recipe
directions: Follow instructions carefully on can, then eat like a man.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and sugar; melt butter, pour over pretzels and sugar; press down.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream sugar and cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Put on top of first layer. Pour boiling water over jello.
Add strawberries, stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until it begins to gel.
Pour over second layer.

title: mexican potato salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into bite-size chunks.
Boil until tender and set aside.
Fry bacon until very crispy.
Drain and set aside.
Saute diced green onion in oleo until tender.
Melt cheese and add milk.
Stir until smooth, then add green onions and crushed bacon to cheese mix.
Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish and pour cheese mixture over potatoes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: pork chop and rice bake
directions: In skillet brown chops on both sides in oil.
Season with pepper.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: First, fill a large cookie sheet with graham crackers, divided in fourths.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and butter; cook exactly 3 minutes after all has melted.
Remove from heat; add chopped pecans, then with a spoon, drizzle mixture over crackers. Cook for 10 minutes and no more.
They burn easily.

title: almond-date pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chops and lower temperature to simmer.
Simmer for 45 to 60 minutes until tender.

title: easy skillet supper
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix, rice, water and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or longer.
If you use onion and bell pepper, saute with ground beef.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots 15 minutes in hot water to cover.
Cut up apricots and dates.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with fruit and nuts.
Add liquids and beat well.
Turn into greased loaf pan and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: beth's baked beans
directions: Brown together hamburger, bacon and onion; drain well.
Drain juice from kidney beans and butter beans and save.
Mix hamburger mixture with the beans and seasonings.
Stir back in enough juice to make a moist mixture (about half).
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.
Can be frozen.

title: deep dish lasagne
directions: Remove casing from sausage and mix with beef; fry in its own juice.
Add garlic salt, chopped parsley, basil, salt, whole tomatoes and tomato paste and let simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, vanilla, butter and buttermilk and mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 5 minutes in preheated 425° oven, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until toothpick comes out clean, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; spread on buns. Add ham and cheese on each bun. Wrap in foil. Heat at 350° for 5 minutes. Can be frozen. Place directly from freezer into oven at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: annette's broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per directions; drain.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: b-52's
directions: Cook ground beef and season with pepper, salt and garlic powder.
Feel free to add Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce or anything else.

title: cheddar cheese twists
directions: Separate rolls into individual rectangles.
Combine cheese, oregano and red pepper; blend well.
Sprinkle evenly over each rectangle.
Grasp top right hand corner and bottom left hand corner of rectangle and twist in opposite directions and stretch to an 8-inch length.
Place on buttered cookie sheet, pressing ends down slightly.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with butter.

title: st. nikolaas koekjes(santa claus cookies)
directions: Add soda to sour cream.
Mix all ingredients together and knead into a loaf.
Set away overnight.
Roll out on floured board to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters and bake in a moderate oven, 350°.

title: tomato tortellini soup
directions: Mix tomato soup as usual.
Chop vegetables in bite-size pieces. Cook tortellini al dente.
Combine in large pot.
Season as you wish.
Add cayenne pepper or Tabasco sauce.
Use your imagination. Quick and easy.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken and garlic; cook and stir for 4 to 5 minutes, or until chicken is no
longer pink.
Add ginger, 1/2 cup water, soy sauce and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta and frozen vegetables, returning to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes, or until pasta and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: creamy frosting
directions: *Brown sugar may be substituted for the white sugar. Especially good on spice cake.

title: carole's sauerbraten(from a friend from new york)
directions: Pour over eye of round roast.
Place in fridge.
Turn in mixture several times a day for 5 days.
On fifth day, place in Dutch oven with juices.
Cook slowly until tender.
Remove from liquid and refrigerate.
When cold, slice in very thin slices.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Set aside. Add sugar gradually to shortening.
Blend in eggs, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.
Blend in the sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Turn into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan, well-greased on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: harvard beets
directions: Prepare and cook beets.
Cut into slices.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in beets; heat through. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In heavy saucepan, place oleo, chocolate, milk, Crisco, corn syrup, salt and sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil; stir very little, to keep from sticking.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Beat just a little, until slightly thick, then pour over cake.

title: quick tuna-macaroni bake(microwave)
directions: Combine macaroni and cheese with 1 1/2 cups hot water in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid. Microwave on High 4 to 4 1/2 minutes, or until mixture boils. Stir in canned soup, tuna fish (drained), milk, butter or margarine and parsley.
Cover, microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring once.
Top with French fried onions, if desired.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: mustard beans
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, thoroughly stir together the sugar, flour, mustard, celery seed, salt and turmeric.
Gradually stir in vinegar, keeping smooth.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and boiling.
Add beans, mix in gently.
Cool.
Refrigerate, covered, until flavors blend.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and bake cornbread mix according to directions.
Crumble bread mix with squash and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: variety baked beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, until beans are juicy and bubbly.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Secure one large elephant.
Kill, clean and cut into small cubes (this will take about two months).
Put in large kettle and simmer over kerosene heat at 465° for 14 weeks.
Make gravy to cover.
This serves 3,685 people.
If more meat is needed, add two rabbits.
But use only if necessary, as few people care for hare in their stew.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Line a casserole dish with raw hamburger.
Layer rest of ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: bean dip
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add chili and cheese; stir until melted.
Serve warm with chips.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Mix and layer in casserole chilies and cheeses.
Then mix eggs, milk, flour and salt and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: laura's chicken
directions: You will need an electric frying pan.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Put into empty coffee can; cover.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour or barbecue on top of grill.

title: mocha chiffon pie
directions: *Use type of milk in your diet plan (skim, 2 %).

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon flour with Comstock apples.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt with fork.
Add egg to mixture.
It will become "crumbly looking."
Spread mixture over apples.
Pour 1/4 pound margarine over mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve plain or with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Follow instructions on jello package to dissolve jello.
Add drained pineapple in place of some of the water for jello.
Add oranges, walnuts and cranberries.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cut in soft margarine.
Add milk, egg, vanilla and lemon juice.
When mixture is combined if it's not stiff, add more flour until stiff.
Roll dough mixture about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut desired shape.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well. Finish with water to make 1 gallon.

title: oven beef stroganoff
directions: Combine ingredients in covered baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: hot fudge
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla to mixture after it boils.
Pour over ice cream.

title: coconut chews
directions: Mix flour, butter and 2 tablespoons brown sugar as for pie crust; put in bottom of pan.
Mix eggs, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Pour over crust mixture and bake for 20 minutes (to 25 minutes) at 350°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, cocoa, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture with water and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes in square pan. Spread with icing while cake is warm.

title: stack pies
directions: Combine ingredients except pie shells.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cook about 20 minutes at 350° or until thickened.
Stack on one on another, putting caramel between layers as icing.

title: onion casserole
directions: Butter a flat 2-quart baking dish.
Boil onions in water until tender; drain.
Line the baking dish with toast, crust removed. Cover with a layer of onions and a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat layer of toast; cover with layer of onions then layer of cheese. At this point casserole may be covered with plastic wrap and stored in refrigerator for the day.
Beat egg slightly and add balance of ingredients.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: banana-pineapple tea ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 10-inch tube or Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all together in blender or mixer.
Pour into 10-inch greased pan (no flour).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as box directs.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut on bottom of pan.
Spread cake mix over top.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add beaten eggs, coloring and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times (not soda).
Add alternately with buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Beat in soda and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use 3 greased and floured cake pans (round).

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Add to mixture.
Stir until moistened. Add onion, half the cheese and parsley.
Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle melted butter over.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: patriotic punch
directions: Pour berry mix into 3 plastic ice trays and freeze, 3 hours or overnight, until frozen.

title: 5 can chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Crumble potato chips on top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican tossed pasta salad
directions: Bring water and bouillon granules to boil.
Stir in pasta and cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute garlic in oil 1 minute; add chicken and saute 3 to 4 minutes or until chicken is barely cooked.
Stir in red pepper, green onions, olives and chilies.
Cook until peppers are crisp but tender. Remove from heat; toss with pasta and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with salsa.

title: german potato bake
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, 1/4 pound cheese and margarine.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add 2 tablespoons bacon, 2 tablespoons onion, salad dressing, sour cream and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese, bacon and onions.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pink pineapple salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Sprinkle Jell-O over these ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a container with lid and chill.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding according to package directions, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half of the pudding over graham crackers, then top with more crackers. Put in rest of pudding and top with another layer of crackers.
Frost and chill overnight.
It is easier to put frosting on crackers before placing them on top of the pudding.

title: collard greens with hot pepper sauce
directions: Slice meat into 1/8-inch strips and fry until crisp in cast-iron pot to render 1/2 cup grease.
Pull collard leaves from main stalk.
Wash both sides of leaves thoroughly.
Remove center stem from each leaf.
Heat grease on low (do not add water).
Fill pot with greens and sprinkle liberally with salt.
Cover.
When cooked down, add more greens.
Sprinkle with salt and stir from bottom of pot.
Repeat until all leaves are in pot, stirring occasionally.
After 30 minutes, taste and add salt as needed. Cook for total of 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: sue's blueberry delight
directions: Mix with spoon Bisquick, soft butter, 1/2 cup sugar and stir until crumbly; add pecans.
Put into pan, smooth out and press down.
Do not need to grease pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Drain berries.
Mix in saucepan 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir and add water gradually, stirring over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
As it thickens, add blueberries and boil for one minute, stirring constantly.
Set aside until cool; should be a little thick.
Whip cream cheese and Cool Whip together with mixer until smooth.
Drain pineapple and spread layer of pineapple on top of crust; next put 1/2 of cream cheese topping and then all of blueberry topping.
Add rest of cream cheese topping and pecans on top, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy party pizza
directions: Spread large flour tortilla with pizza sauce.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Add the desired meat topping.
If using sausage or hamburger, cook in skillet until brown and crumbly, then drain. Bake pizzas in 400° oven until hot and cheese bubbles, about 5 minutes.

title: bacon cheese roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cheese and parsley. Spread onto each slice of bread.
Roll lengthwise and cut in half. Wrap each with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until bacon is done.

title: mulled wine california style
directions: Combine everything but the wine, brandy and the garnish.
Boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes; strain.
Add wine and brandy.
Bring to simmer over low heat. Ladle into heated mugs and add garnish.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Remove from oven and immediately poke 35 to 40 holes in cake with handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour on condensed milk and spread evenly.
Pour on caramel topping and spread evenly. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with crushed candy bars the next day.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach or broccoli.
Simmer onion in oleo until tender.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Make into 1-inch balls (about 36).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until set.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: curried shrimp sandwich
directions: Spread small rectangle of Melba toast with butter or mayonnaise.
Cover each with a piece of Boston lettuce cut to size.
Arrange thin wedge of Gouda or Edam cheese over lettuce and top with a halved, seeded red grape, cut side down.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and 1/2 gallon milk.
May use chocolate or any kind of fruit you like.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat tomato soup in 3-quart saucepan.
Dissolve Knox gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water, then add to soup.
Add cream cheese to soup mixture.
Stir until creamy.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into greased mold and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground meat.
Pour off fat.
Line a 2-quart baking dish with meat, then drained beans.
Pour soup over beans and meat. Cover beans with mashed potatoes and dot with butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour or until potatoes are lightly browned.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Crush chips. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Boil chicken until done. Saute broth and debone chicken. Mix cream of chicken soup, some broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes together. Add cheese. Make layers of chips, soup mixture, chicken and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kings ranch chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Mix together chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and tomatoes and peppers in bowl.
Make layer of chicken in casserole dish and pour 1/2 of liquid over top.
Add 1/2 of tortillas, cheese and onion. Make a second layer of the same.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: eggplant parmesan(or zucchini or chicken)
directions: Slice eggplant; salt both sides and let stand on counter for 1 hour (takes bitter taste and water out).
Wash thoroughly after 1 hour.
Pat dry.
Dip eggplant in egg and then bread crumbs (both sides).
Brown both sides in hot oil; drain eggplant on brown bag. Layer in Pyrex, sauce first, layer eggplant, layer shredded Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Make two or three layers of each.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a pie pan with Crisco.
Sprinkle lightly with 1 tablespoon of corn meal.
In bowl, mix together rest of ingredients; pour into pie pan and bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook, peel and mash potatoes while hot.
Add butter and eggs. Add milk, lemon, cinnamon and nutmeg and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° until set.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate over hot water; cool. (May add few drops hot water to prevent hardening.) Cream butter and sugar; add melted chocolate and then eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add pecans, coconut and cherries, then vanilla.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Needs no frosting.

title: cabbage ramen salad
directions: Break up the noodles and toast with the almonds and sesame seed without oil.
Mix together the sugar, Ramen seasoning, oil and wine vinegar.
Chicken cut into small pieces can be added. Best made the day before.

title: nibbles
directions: Mix together the margarine, Worcestershire and salts; pour mix over the first 4 ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Put half of mixture from large bowl in well-greased angel food pan.
Add most of apples, then the rest of mixture and then remaining apples on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cake will come out plain looking.

title: spinach and grits casserole
directions: Cook grits and spinach; drain.
Mix with cheese.
Add soup mix.
Put eggs in a cup.
Add milk on top to make 1 cup and mix. Put all in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or crispy brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Just before serving add one bottle of ginger ale.

title: cherre's pineapple crunch cake
directions: Spread pineapple in oblong pan.
Smooth cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Melt oleo and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle a layer of coconut and then a layer of pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna dip
directions: Thoroughly drain tuna and flake with fork.
Combine all ingredients, except tuna and mix until blended.
Add tuna and mix well.
Serve with raw vegetables and crackers of your choice. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain off fat.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water.
Add soups to meat.
Mix well.
Add canned mushrooms and sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 3 parts.
Use 3 pieces of aluminum foil and shape each part of meat mixture in long roll. Roll up in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Take out, turn over, and poke hole in bottom of each roll with fork.
Place on rack in pan and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and quarter apples, place in medium saucepan.
Pour water over apples, bring to a boil, reduce to simmer, cover and cook about 10 minutes, until apples are tender, but not mushy.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg, brown sugar and butter.
Use potato masher or food processor to blend mixture.
Serve warm or chilled, can be frozen.

title: stella's cheese cake
directions: Blend Ricotta and cream cheese in a bowl.
Add sugar to the mixture gradually, continuously mixing.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, flour, cornstarch and melted butter.
Blend until smooth, then add the sour cream and blend again.
Pour into a 9-inch greased spring-form pan.
Put cake into cold oven, then bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn off oven and let cake stay in oven for 2 more hours until the oven is cool.
Remove and place on a rack.
Do not open oven door once cake is inside.

title: water whip pie crust
directions: Put shortening in a bowl.
Add milk and boiling water.
Whip with a fork until mixture looks like whipped cream.
Then add flour and salt.
Mix and form into a ball.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Microwave chips 2 1/2 minutes and stir.
May need to microwave 1 1/2 to 2 more minutes. Stir until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows until melted and smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: pedro's special
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion and garlic.
Set aside and mix tomato sauce, tomato juice, oregano and chili powder.
Set aside and mix kidney beans and corn chips.
Layer 3 mixtures in layers in order listed.
Bake 45 minutes, covered, at 350°. Uncover last 10 minutes.
Top with chips, shredded lettuce and onion and grated cheese.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine chicken, salt, onion and celery in a large stockpot. Cover with water; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes or until done.
Reserve broth for stew.
When chicken is cool, remove skin, debone and cut into bite size pieces.

title: orange cinnamon biscuits
directions: Grease Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter; melt remainder of stick.
Place marmalade evenly in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle nuts into pan.
In separate bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter then in sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on edge in pan spacing evenly.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool upright for 5 minutes then dump on platter.

title: bread or rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with 1 teaspoon sugar for 10 minutes. Scald milk and add to sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add yeast and stir. Add 4 cups flour.
Blend smooth.
Add shortening.
Blend well; add remaining flour.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and let rise again.

title: pistachio cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together; shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Store in plastic bag.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: mom's sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburger and chopped onion; drain.
Add ketchup, sugar and mustard.
Cook at high temperature, stirring constantly. Ketchup will thicken.
Let completely cool.
(That's the secret.) Reheat at meal time.
Serve on hamburger buns or on a bed of your favorite chips.

title: graham cracker fluff pudding
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Let stand.
Cook 1/2 cup sugar, milk and egg yolks together.
Cook a few minutes.
Then mix in gelatin and vanilla.
Set in a cool place until thickened.
Add egg whites and whipped cream.
Mix well and let cool.
Crush graham crackers.
Mix with oleo and sugar.
Put on top and bottom.

title: etoy's dumplings
directions: Cut
flour,
salt
and shortening together.
Add enough milk to hold together.
Roll and cut into strips and drop into seasoned chicken and stock.	Stir occasionally.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: In a medium bowl, mix beaten eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into 5 ounce custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set cups in a shallow baking pan.
Pour boiling water around the cups.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pan (either an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square or round).
Place apple slices in pan. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with light cream or ice cream, if desired.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.
A good recipe.
Quick!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix gelatin, pudding and water and bring to boil.
Cool until nearly set.
Whip this mixture and fold in the Cool Whip.
Fold in sliced strawberries and fill
pie shell.
Refrigerate until set. Garnish with whipped cream and whole berries.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and milk in flat Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle a little cheese on top.
Place in microwave until bubbly.

title: spicy cajun rice salad
directions: Bring water and salt to a full boil in a medium saucepan. Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.
Cool.
Combine salad dressing, pepper sauce and mustard in small bowl.
Blend well.
Combine rice with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Spoon dressing mixture over salad, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bent peanut butter sandwichsocorro, new mexico
directions: Spread peanut butter on half of it.
Spread jelly on the other half and bend it over.

title: best ever cider
directions: Use crock pot or large pan on stove.
Mix in 1 gal. of apple cider, 1 qt. of cranberry juice, 2 c. brown sugar, and 3 to 4 sticks of cinnamon.
Heat on medium heat for 15 minutes until all ingredients are mixed well and cinnamon sticks have time to flavor cider.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the crushed pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Mix the cream cheese, sugar and whipped topping; spread on cooled mix.
Mix well the strawberry jello, boiling water and frozen strawberries.
Pour over cheese layer.
Let mixture jell slightly 10 minutes in refrigerator.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Top with crackers and dab with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: chewy noels
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs lightly with fork.
Combine next 3 ingredients and add to beaten egg.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Cut into triangles.

title: pink squirrel
directions: Mix all together and enjoy.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, margarine, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg thoroughly.
Blend all dry ingredients and add. Roll dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Flatten crisscross style with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.
Makes 3 dozen, 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Crumble cake into bowl.
Make pudding.
Pour over cake; layer fruit as desired.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mom's bean salad(very good)
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper together well.
Let rest for 24 hours before serving; overnight is better if you have the time.
Keep refrigerated.

title: skinny strawberry shake
directions: Just Before Serving:
In blender at high speed, blend all ingredients until smooth. Serve in tall glass. Makes 1 serving.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all sausage, cheese and biscuit mix together and put into balls.
Cook until they seem done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into small casserole dish (lightly greased). Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: four bean salad
directions: In large bowl, combine vinegar, oil, sugar and pepper.
Add beans and onion.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 4 hours.
Makes 8 cups or 16 servings. Serve heated, chilled or at room temperature.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour, margarine and water.
Pour into any size baking type bowl.
Pour can of peaches on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until top is lightly browned.

title: apple flan
directions: Combine flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and the salt.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until particles resemble small peas.
Sprinkle with ice water; mix lightly with fork.
Form into balls.
Flatten into 6-inch circle. Wrap and chill at least 1 1/2 hours or until firm enough to roll.
Toss apples with lemon juice and remaining 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Using lightly floured stockinette-covered rolling pin, roll out pastry 1/8-inch thick on cookie sheet.
Place 9-inch layer cake pan on pastry.
Cut around edge with knife or pastry wheel.
Remove excess pastry and reserve.
Prick dough with fork and bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes or until golden.
Cool on cookie sheet on rack.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Cool 10 minutes.
Combine pickle relish, ham and pimentos.
Cool completely and stir in mayonnaise.

title: millionaires candy
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels and oleo with hot water. Remove from heat and add pecans and chill until firm.
In double boiler, melt paraffin and milk chocolate bar.
With spoon, dip caramel candy in chocolate mixture and drop on wax paper to cool.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Stir in cake flour and baking powder.
Grease a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans.
Pour batter into pan; bake at 325° for 70 to 80 minutes. Cool in pan 5 to 10 minutes before inverting.

title: citrus blossom punch(serves 24)
directions: Mix preceding in large pitcher or pan.

title: pork chop one dish meal
directions: Brown chops in shortening, adding 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper when chops are turned.
Add vegetables, water and remaining salt and pepper.
Cover and continue cooking over low heat for 1 hour or until meat is fork-tender.

title: easy as pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: ginny's mexican casserole
directions: Brown the meat and onion in a skillet. Drain fat. Combine rest of the ingredients except tortillas and cheese. Add to meat mixture.
In a Pyrex casserole dish, layer the meat sauce, tortillas, meat sauce, tortillas and end with a layer of meat mixture. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Top casserole with cheese and bake just long enough to melt the cheese.

title: clam chowder
directions: Grind clams.
Add clams, potatoes and onions; cook.
Cook celery until well done (separately).
Add to clam mixture.
Add peas; cook until tender.
Add milk and thicken; do not cook after adding milk, it curdles.
Heat tomatoes and add soda.
Put to soup last.
Add parsley.

title: pound cake fix up
directions: Slice a frozen loaf pound cake, thawed, horizontally in half. Spread soft style cream cheese on bottom layer; then top with preserves (your choice).
Replace top layer of cake.
Top with soft style cream cheese and melted preserves.

title: sausage fruit cake
directions: Soak raisins in hot water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Put hot water in bowl with sausage.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in loaf or Bundt pan.

title: dinner salad
directions: Whip vinaigrette, mustard, olive oil, salt, sugar, pepper and garlic with a fork until creamy.
Lightly toss cabbage and Brussels sprouts.
Top with the dressing.
Follow with crumbled Bleu cheese.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; blend in milk.
Stir in cornbread mix, cheese, corn, onion, oil, sugar and baking powder.
Blend. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: amish apple pie
directions: Slice apples thin.
Put apples, water and cinnamon in greased casserole.
Blend flour, sugar and butter into crumbs.
Spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until apples are tender, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Remove and pour off fat.
Make glaze and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender (add a touch of oil and 2 teaspoons of butter to prevent sticking together).
Brown ground chuck and onion; drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Take off heat.
Mix sauce with macaroni.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, oleo and nuts.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Arrange chicken skin side down in a foil lined pan.
Mix together honey, mustard and curry powder.
Brush chicken well with sauce.
Turn chicken every 10 minutes.
Broil until done and nicely browned, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: nita's zucchini crab  cakes
directions: Squeeze zucchini as dry as possible.
Mix with other ingredients.
Make into cakes.
Dust with flour.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add zucchini, onion, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and rosemary.
Saute mixture over medium heat, stir often until zucchini is tender (20 minutes).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Cream the margarine and Crisco together.
Add sugar and eggs in mixing bowl. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: butter horn rolls
directions: Soften the dry yeast in warm water 110°.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, then flour; mix to smooth dough.

title: crabmeat cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Drain crabmeat and add chopped green onions and mayonnaise, then add to melted cheese. Serve hot with Melba rounds or chips.

title: ritz unbaked fruit cake
directions: Mix milk and marshmallows and heat until melted in large pan. Add remaining ingredients to milk mixture.
Mix well.
Pack back into cracker box.
Store in refrigerator for 2 days before slicing.

title: marshmallow fluff
directions: Add marshmallows and 1/4 pound walnuts, broken, to cream and mix all together.
Will serve 8.
White grapes or pineapple may be added, also.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours.
Very good winter dish.

title: christmas red beets
directions: Clean; cook 1/2 hour.
Peel and cut beets and place in jars.

title: vegetable stuffed shells
