directions: Cook shells in boiling water approximately 7 minutes. Transfer to cool water and let stand until ready to use.
Melt butter.
Saute zucchini, broccoli, mushrooms, carrots and scallions, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, water and cocoa to a boil.
While still hot, add flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth, then add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into a 15 x 10 1/2 inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Ice cake while it is still hot.

title: cheesy potato balls
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done.
Peel and place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt, cover with grated cheese.
Place
under
broiler
or in oven
to
melt
cheese. Garnish with minced parsley and paprika
just
before serving. Serves 4.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, sour milk, cocoa and shortening together.
Mix well, then add the hot water, containing soda.
Mix, then bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently or beat vigorously 300 strokes by hand. Batter will be very thick.
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour slightly less than 1/2 of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt butter, milk and caramels in top of a double boiler.
Cool slightly, then pour over cake.
Pour remaining cake batter over caramel.
Top with pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Check with toothpick to see if top layer of cake is done.)
It may take up to 35 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; blend well.
Slowly add hot milk. Pour in crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 425° for 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion in large bowl.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and chicken flavoring packet.
Beat with wire whisk until sugar is dissolved.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 to 2 hours.
Shortly before serving, break up noodles; add with almonds and sesame seed.
Toss gently.
Makes 24 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until thick.
Add oil gradually and combine thoroughly.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Stir in carrots and blend well.
Turn into 2 well-greased loaf pans or 3 (1-pound) coffee cans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Good hot, cold or toasted.
Can be doubled or frozen.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; cut in butter.
Add sweet potatoes.
Add milk.
Cut out.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: ham macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Rinse in cool water.
Mix all together.
Can serve on bed of lettuce.
Garnish with boiled eggs.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients and then add egg, vanilla and butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salad on a shoestring
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Cover and chill.
Add shoestring potatoes just before serving.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 45 minutes until sides start to leave the edge and middle is bubbling.
Cut into small squares while still slightly warm.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil and cook the lasagna noodles until tender, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Spread out flat until ready to use.
Blend tomato paste and garlic; beat at medium speed until smooth. Combine cheese with eggs and Parmesan.
To assemble the casserole, layer about 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish coated with nonstick spray.
Place 1/3 of the lasagna noodles across the bottom of the dish, overlapping. Spread half the cheese mixture over the noodles.
Top with another third of noodles.
Layer the remaining cheese and noodles and pour the rest of the sauce over the noodles.
Spread Mozzarella on top. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake large potatoes until done.
While hot, slice potato in 1/2 longwise.
With a spoon, scoop out the inside and put in a mixing bowl.
Place potato shell on a baking dish.
Add sour cream, margarine, salt, pepper and milk to taste.
Whip until creamy with electric mixer.
Put filling back into potato shells. Sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until hot throughout potato.
These are great prepared in advance and heated at the last minute.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Place pecan halves in bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt. Gently pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350°
and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread and bagel chips) together and chill 1 hour.
Put mixture in middle of bread on large plate or round tray.
Cut up the middle of the bread and put around dip with bagel chips.
Tastes better than it sounds!!!

title: layered chalupa dip
directions: Combine beans and taco sauce in a small saucepan; mix well. Heat thoroughly.
Spread in a serving platter.
Peel, seed and mash avocados; blend in lemon juice, oil and garlic salt.
Spread over bean layer.
Layer next 6 ingredients over avocado layer. Serve with chips.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook sausage in water; slice.
Brown ground meat and onion. Add spices, tomato, sauce and 1 cup water and sausage; simmer. Mix cheese and parsley (drain cheese).
Cook lasagne.
Arrange in casserole in layers of meat, noodles, cheese and noodles.
Repeat and top with cheese.

title: crackerjack cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Blend in sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder and soda.
Stir in oatmeal and coconut.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: brown potatoes
directions: Thinly slice potatoes.
Melt butter in large skillet; add potatoes and brown over medium heat.
Season to taste.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add 4 egg yolks; blend until smooth.
Melt the chocolate; add to creamed mixture. Sift flour and salt; add alternately with the buttermilk.
Mix the hot water with the soda; pour into the batter and mix.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Use two 9-inch pans.

title: scalloped rhubarb
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Stir in bread cubes.
Cut rhubarb into small pieces and add with sugar or honey. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheesy corn chowder for one
directions: Fry bacon in 1 1/2-quart saucepan until crisp; remove and drain.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon bacon fat from saucepan.
Stir onion and celery into fat in saucepan.
Cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in corn, milk, seasoned salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Drain spinach.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 13x9-inch greased pan and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: texas lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let cool, stirring occasionally.
Mix together cake mix, Wesson oil, eggs and lemon extract.
Beat 2 minutes, then add jello.
Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Chop and combine olives, onions and tomatoes.
Add Italian dressing and garlic salt.
Refrigerate several hours before serving with tortilla chips or saltine crackers.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Wash and place cucumbers into two 1-quart jars.
Mix other ingredients well and pour over cucumbers.
Tighten lids and refrigerate at least one week before serving.
Can be kept refrigerated for 3 months.

title: canned green tomato mincemeat for pies or cookies
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Discard juice.
Cover with cold water.
Boil 5 minutes. Drain.
Add chopped suet and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in sugar and boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and boil rapidly until thick, stirring so it won't scorch, for about 20 minutes.
Pack and seal immediately in quart or pint jars as you prefer.

title: coconut candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Heat until sugar is melted.
Then boil 5 minutes longer.
Stir in coconut; beat and pour.
Cool.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large pan; add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat or microwave.
Using buttered, waxed paper, press mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour, 1/2 cup nuts and 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° (until lightly browned).
Let cool.

title: eric gwinns barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients in roasting pan. Cook 5 to 6 hours in 300° oven. Meat will fall apart with fork.

title: master mix
directions: Stir baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar into flour.
Sift together three times into a large mixing bowl or onto a large square of plain paper.
Cut in the shortening until mix is the consistency of cornmeal.
Store in covered container at room temperature.
To measure the Master Mix, pile it lightly into cup and level with a spatula.
Makes 13 cups.

title: hot chicken salad(makes 12 servings)
directions: Combine everything except cheese and potato chips. Put in greased baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top, then chips. Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Add all ingredients in large pan and mix well.
Add 3 to 4 quarts of hot broth and mix well.
Do not make too thin.
Bake in well-greased roaster pan for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 20.

title: steak tamale casserole
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares and brown in oil.
Add liquor from mushrooms, bouillon cubes, tomato sauce and onion.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove cover and cook liquid down to 1/2 cup.
Add corn, mushrooms, olives and tamales cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix very lightly.
Turn into greased baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serves 8.

title: new orleans chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with thyme.
Add salt and pepper to taste. In large skillet, brown chicken in oil for 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook over medium-high heat until thickened and chicken is done.

title: ranch loaf(bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt and wheat flour; beat.
Cover.
Let rise 30 minutes. Dissolve dry milk in water; bring to boil and add sugars, molasses and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir sponge down; add rest and half the
whole wheat flour.
Beat well; add enough more flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and cover.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Knead 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double.
Make into 2 loaves; place in greased bread tins.
Let rise.
Bake in 350° oven for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: rotel dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except sausage.
Microwave 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add meat.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: hash browns
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Can sprinkle more grated cheese on top, if desired.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain excess fat.
Put in large dish with remaining ingredients and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Good in crock-pot, too.

title: camper's stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Mix all ingredients and place in a covered roaster.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 6 hours.
Check for doneness and enjoy!

title: salmon spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pie shell 10 minutes until partially set.

title: yard bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients gently.
Bubbles will work better if they can sit for at least 15 minutes.
Any quantity can be made by using a 3 part water to 1 part soap ratio.
One tablespoon of glycerine is needed for each cup of soap used.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Heat margarine and oil in 425° oven.
Coat chicken with flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Bake 20 minutes and then turn.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Lower heat to 375° and bake 45 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and serve over rice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk together.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Layer half of pudding mixture in bowl and top with half of fruit.
Next, top with remaining pudding mixture and then remaining fruit.
(I use strawberries, grapes, bananas and kiwi.)
Any fruit combination will do.

title: mexicana layered dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix beans, cheese and 2 tablespoons of the onions and seasonings in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated; top with teaspoonfuls of sour cream, tomatoes and remaining onion.
Serve with green, red or yellow pepper wedges or chips of your choice.
Makes 4 cups.

title: alma's spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender in water.
Pick off of bone; saute celery, onion and peppers in oleo.
Melt cheese in spaghetti; mix in all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes enough for a crowd!

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add egg and bananas.
Add oats and optional nuts.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add to rest of dough.
Drop by spoon on lightly greased pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Enjoy.

title: ham and turkey casserole
directions: Melt butter. Stir in flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Add milk and cream. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Stir in remaining ingredients, except nuts. Turn into 2-quart casserole. Top with almonds. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Melt cheese, butter and milk until smooth.
Put potatoes in large casserole dish and pour sauce over potatoes.
Let stand one hour.
Cover and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Uncover for last 10 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt together about 10 minutes.
Place okra in pint jars.
Put clove of garlic and a pod of pepper in top of jars.
Sprinkle spices in jars.
Pour hot liquid into jars. Let cool and seal.
Put jars aside at least 3 weeks for pickling process to take place. Chill before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Cream together.
Add eggs, then flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and applesauce.
Mix well. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Grease a baking pan and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: carol's addictive goodies
directions: *You can substitute other flavor morsels. However, butterscotch makes the best impact on the pallette.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and soda and cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by teaspoon on salted waxed paper.
Cool.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour boiling water over mixture, stir until shortening is dissolved.
Add eggs.
Mix warm water with yeast.
Mix flour, one cup at a time, and beat well.
Dough should be soft, not stiff.
Cover and put in warm place to rise.
Takes one hour or longer.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Beat
eggs
and
add
milk
and
seasonings.
Grease
a casserole and
add	a layer of crumbs.
Add a layer of oysters (1/2
pint).
Repeat
with another layer of crumbs and oysters (1/2 pint).
Pour egg mixture over top.
Add melted margarine, drizzled over top layer.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed salmon florentine
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Add flour; cook without browning for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add milk slowly, whisk until thick and smooth. Add sherry and set aside.
Blanch spinach; pat dry and chop. Saute in 6 tablespoons butter for one minute.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Saute 5 more minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted. Combine with sherry sauce.
Place plastic wrap directly on sauce and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut slit in salmon making pocket.
Fill with sauce mixture and secure slot closed with toothpick.
Place in shallow buttered baking dish. Squeeze lemon juice over.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Drizzle with butter.
Pour wine and water into bottom of pan; bake 10 to 12 minutes and garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.
Serves 6 people.

title: squash casserole
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except the stuffing mix.
Pour half of stuffing mix in buttered casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture over this.
Add remaining stuffing mix; dot with butter. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: To cooked and drained hamburger, add taco mix and water. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place package of rolls on bottom and sides of pie pan.
Crunch Doritos on bottom of rolls.
Place hamburger mixture on top; followed by cheese.
Top with crushed Doritos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; serve with sour cream and black olives on top.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly and pat into a cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and beat well.
Gradually add sifted flour and vanilla; beat for 3 minutes.
Then add egg whites while beating and add nuts. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 35 minutes in tube pan.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Place alternate layers of potatoes, tuna, soup and peas.
Crumble potato chips and sprinkle on top. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Stir in other ingredients.
Be sure to cut up candy bars into small pieces. Add to mixture.
Mix well.

title: chocolate whipped cream filling
directions: Mix egg yolks, water and chocolate.
Spread 3 tablespoons over cooled oleo.
Chill remainder.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and cream. Beat until thick.
Spread half over chocolate in pie shell. Combine remaining whipped cream with the chocolate mixture. Spread over whipped cream in pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours. Very good.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Bisquick and sugar in large mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine egg, orange peel, orange juice and oil.
Add to Bisquick and beat with wooden spoon until mixture is smooth.
Stir in wheat germ, 2/3 cup chocolate chips, raisins, cherries and nuts.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Take chicken from bone and chop into bite-size pieces.
Put into large bowl.
Add onions, peppers, soups and gradually stir in broth.
Line casserole with tortillas; cover with mixture.
Repeat layers until full.
Bake until lightly browned or sets, approximately 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven and cook until cheese melts.

title: gingerbread
directions: Add
beaten eggs to sugar, molasses and melted shortening. Add
flour
sifted
with
other dry ingredients and mix. Add hot water last.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes in greased pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook shells and Spam.
Chop onion and pepper.
Mix altogether.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Chop vegetables and cover with water. Add milk, ham and cheese sauce. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: cabbage meatballs
directions: Mix in bowl the chuck, rice, chopped green peppers, onion, celery, shredded cabbage, salt and pepper.
Mix together and make into large meatballs.
Place in baking dish or casserole.
Pour tomato soup and water over it.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sunday morning omelet
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Break into pieces.
You can use ham or sausage.
Cut cheese into halves and arrange on slightly buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add chopped bacon. Pour over cheese and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bev's popover pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat egg.
Add flour.
Gradually add milk until smooth.
Melt butter in shallow pan until bubbly; pour in batter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
(If you have used extra milk, lower temperature to 350° after 10 minutes; bake until done.)
Top with maple syrup, powdered sugar, fruit or jam.

title: orange sangria
directions: Cut
orange
in half.
Cut 1 or 2 slices from one half, and then into quarters, and save for garnish.
With a vegetable peeler,
thinly
slice
outer
peel
of the other half of orange.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let chill until firm.

title: candy coconut balls
directions: Mix all together and make into balls. Melt chocolate chips and 3/4 cake of canning wax. Dip coconut balls into chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. Add the zucchini and walnuts. Sift the flour. Mix well. Makes 2 loaves. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers and combine with 1 tablespoon of sugar and margarine; press into a pie pan or any container.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping.
Press remaining mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, building up 1/2 inch edges. Spread pie filling over cake mixture to within 1/2 inch of edges. Mix walnuts with reserved cake mixture.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: onion chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop French fried onion rings until they become crumbs.
Dip chicken breast in egg white, then into onion ring crumbs.	Coat well.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: macaroni and dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This makes a large amount and is very rich.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve cold.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in oil in large skillet until tender.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix in shrimp. Heat 15 to 20 minutes longer on medium-low.
Serve hot over rice. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: maryland stuffed ham
directions: If skin is still on ham, remove by paring with sharp knife. Leave skin on hock end.
With fat side up, pierce with long, thin knife, a row of slits, about 1-inch apart, as deep as possible without going through bottom.
On second row, stagger the slits (like bricklaying) from first roll, off center.
Continue piercing rows as far back as possible.

title: sugar cookies
directions: *If shortening is used, increase salt to 1 teaspoon.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Toss shrimp into salt and pepper mixture to coat.
Heat oil in wok or large nonstick skillet.
Add shrimp; stir over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Move to rim of wok, or remove from skillet. Add garlic and green onion to oil and stir-fry 1 minute.
Add pea pods, assorted vegetables and chicken broth; stir over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Stir in shrimp and cook, stirring, for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth, leaving it somewhat soupy. Lightly brown celery, pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons bacon fat. Remove chicken from bone and combine with all other ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated American cheese. Bake 20 minutes (or until bubbly) at 350°.

title: sweet dill strips
directions: Soak for 1 week.

title: basic pie crust
directions: With pastry blender, cut vegetable shortening into flour and salt until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Then add vinegar and mix gently.
Then sprinkle in ice water, a teaspoon at a time, stirring with fork after each addition, until the dough holds together in a moist mass with no dry crumbs.
Chill for a few hours before rolling into crust.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine pudding with pineapple juice and enough water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Boil and cool.
When cool, pour mixture over fruit.

title: dorthea's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; chop in margarine until coarse.
Quickly stir in buttermilk.
On floured surface, knead lightly and roll out to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter or in squares with knife.
Dip tops in margarine melted on cookie sheet and place biscuits close together.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425° until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 large biscuits.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cheese and sugar together well.
(Have cheese and butter soft.)
Put in eggs.
Beat after each egg.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, and beat.
Then add flavoring.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
This is a very moist pound cake and tasty.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and peppers.
Drain.
Add ragu and cream of mushroom soup.
Cook egg noodles for 4 minutes in boiling water, drain.
Add cooked noodles to beef mixture.
Place beef and noodle mix in a deep 9 by 13 inch pan.
Cover with mozzarella and cheddar. Top with pepperoni.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: favorite layer bars
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain 6 lasagna noodles.
Divide sausage into 6 pieces.
Split lengthwise and stuff with 1/2 slice Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap each piece in a noodle.
Place in baking dish and cover with cooking sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: creamy tuna deluxe
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package, only use 3/4 cup milk.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add this plus the remaining ingredients to dinner.
Mix well.
Heat and serve. Yields 6 servings.

title: hash browned scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, potatoes, onions and rest of ingredients.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garbanzo bean salad
directions: Prepare garbanzo beans as per directions on bag.
Chop all vegetables.
Place in large bowl with cooked garbanzo beans.
Add diced chicken and artichoke hearts.
Toss with Beano's White Pizza dressing and lemon juice to taste.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: sauce piquant
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Season fish with salt and pepper.
Place a layer of fish in pan, then layer of onions, etc. Pour remaining ingredients on top of fish.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. begbie's meat loafhouston, texas
directions: Mix together breadcrumbs and milk.
Add the salt and onion. Combine with the ground chuck and ground pork and blend well. Press into loaf pan (2-inch deep X 7 to 7 1/2-inch long).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After 1/2 hour, drain fat and top meat loaf with a layer of barbeque sauce.
Drain fat again at the end of baking.

title: jean's mini ham loaves
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Use no salt. Form into small, oval-shaped loaves (approximately 30 loaves). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Wash
and
seed Damsons.
Measure and add equal amounts of sugar
and just enough water to start cooking.
Boil hard, stirring to
keep
from
sticking
until it is as thick as desired.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(1940)
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in 9-inch iron skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over bottom.
Put pineapple on sugar.

title: tutti-frutti cake
directions: Mix together and cook cake according to package directions.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With fork, mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
In another bowl beat vinegar, egg and water.
Combine two mixtures with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Will be somewhat soggy until mixed for awhile until it forms into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling.
May be kept in refrigerator up to 3 days or frozen until ready to use.
Makes 2 (9-inch) double crust pies and 1 (9-inch) shell.

title: smoked sausage supper
directions: In medium size skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender, do not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and sesaonings.
Simmer on low 10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onions, green pepper, celery and sausage with some margarine until vegetables are tender.
Add rest of ingredients except rice and slow cook (either in crock-pot overnight or bring to boil and then simmer for
1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Serve over the rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and water chestnuts.
Add cooked broccoli.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Shake shrimp, cheese, green onions and flour in paper bag. Place in unbaked pie shell.
Mix the real mayonnaise, eggs and milk.
Pour over shrimp mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cook beans in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Meanwhile, cook onion in butter until soft. Stir in remaining ingredients and blend. Stir in lima beans. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken licken good
directions: Salt chicken; let stand 1 hour.
In the center of a 12-inch square of heavy foil, spread 1 tablespoon butter or margarine. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon onion soup mix.
Place chicken on butter and soup mix.
Sprinkle with remaining soup mix; dot with remaining butter.
Wrap airtight.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: egg-n-biscuit
directions: Scramble the eggs.
Preheat oven to the temperature recommended on the biscuit can.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat Dream Whip with 1 cup milk and vanilla until firm and fluffy.
Add rest of milk and pudding mix; beat on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
While noodles are cooking, beat yolk lightly with fork and add to cream. Quickly heat crab meat in microwave.
Place drained hot noodles in warm serving bowl or platter.
Pour over the noodles the egg and cream mixture.
Add butter, garlic, parsley and half the cheese. Lightly toss.
Add crab meat and gently toss until well blended. Top with remaining cheese.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry-peach pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add dry gelatin, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Cool.
Combine peaches and blueberries in a large bowl.
Add gelatin mixture; toss gently.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Cover and chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, ginger, and cinnamon.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Beat until light.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add molasses and coffee, then sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Roll out on lightly floured board to thickness desired.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place about 1 inch apart on greased baking sheet.
(Pam or vegetable spray works well.)
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Thinner cookies may not take as long to bake.

title: chicken parmesan ii
directions: Roll chicken breasts in beaten egg, lightly salted, then in bread crumbs.
Fry chicken breasts in oil until medium brown. (It's not necessary for the chicken to be cooked completely at this point, since it will be baked later.)
Drain on paper towel and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Heat tomato sauce in sauce pan.
Add basil, garlic, salt and butter.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over chicken breast to cover.
Sprinkle chicken breasts with Parmesan cheese.
Cover pan with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and remove foil.
Cover chicken breasts with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven uncovered.
Continue to bake until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti, linguine or potatoes au gratin.

title: crispy chicken(heart smart)
directions: Cut up frying chicken; remove all skin.
Wash and dry pieces. Season.
Dip each piece in skim milk and roll in corn flakes.
Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Place chicken on oiled pan. Do not crowd.
Bake in preheated oven at 400°.
Crumbs will form a crisp skin.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour; stir in enough pineapple juice to make a thick paste.
Pour pineapple, drained, into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour paste mixture over pineapple; mix well.
Melt margarine.
Stir in crumbled crackers.
Cover top of pineapple mixture with crackers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Great dish with ham.

title: garbage mix(snack)
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy!
Great for snacks or gifts.

title: pea salad
directions: Prepare peas as directed.
Let cool and drain.
Fry bacon, let drain; then crumble.
Break lettuce in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl with cucumber salad dressing.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in floured and greased Bundt pan for 35 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: graham cracker toffee
directions: Lay graham crackers on cookie sheet which has been greased. Boil the margarine, butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour this mixture over graham crackers and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.
Remove immediately onto wax paper.
Enjoy!

title: chicken on rice
directions: Combine liquids.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan generously.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of pan.
Dip chicken into soup and water mixture. Lay chicken over rice.
Pour remaining mixture over chicken. Sprinkle top with dry soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sausage bread
directions: Crumble sausage.
Fry and drain.
Flour work area lightly. Overlap crescent rolls and press together perforations to form a large rectangle.
Roll out dough until approximately 15 x 15-inch.

title: party punch
directions: Heat sugar and water to dissolve.
Cool.
Add juices and bananas.
May be frozen until ready to use.
When ready to serve, mix 2 parts punch base to 1 part 7-Up.
I store in freezer in 1/2 gallon milk cartons.
Use 1/2 gallon punch to 1 quart bottle of 7-Up.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over salad. Toss lightly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind up Spam, pickles and eggs.
Mix mayonnaise to taste.
